INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 1, 'Now King David was old and advanced in years. And although they covered him with clothes, he could not get warm.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 2, 'Therefore his servants said to him, "Let a young woman be sought for my lord the king, and let her wait on the king and be in his service. Let her lie in your arms, that my lord the king may be warm."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 3, 'So they sought for a beautiful young woman throughout all the territory of Israel, and found Abishag the Shunammite, and brought her to the king.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 4, 'The young woman was very beautiful, and she was of service to the king and attended to him, but the king knew her not.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 5, 'Now Adonijah the son of Haggith exalted himself, saying, "I will be king." And he prepared for himself chariots and horsemen, and fifty men to run before him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 6, 'His father had never at any time displeased him by asking, "Why have you done thus and so?" He was also a very handsome man, and he was born next after Absalom.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 7, 'He conferred with Joab the son of Zeruiah and with Abiathar the priest. And they followed Adonijah and helped him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 8, 'But Zadok the priest and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada and Nathan the prophet and Shimei and Rei and David''s mighty men were not with Adonijah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 9, 'Adonijah sacrificed sheep, oxen, and fattened cattle by the Serpent''s Stone, which is beside En-rogel, and he invited all his brothers, the king''s sons, and all the royal officials of Judah,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 10, 'but he did not invite Nathan the prophet or Benaiah or the mighty men or Solomon his brother.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 11, 'Then Nathan said to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon, "Have you not heard that Adonijah the son of Haggith has become king and David our lord does not know it?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 12, 'Now therefore come, let me give you advice, that you may save your own life and the life of your son Solomon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 13, 'Go in at once to King David, and say to him, ''Did you not, my lord the king, swear to your servant, saying, "Solomon your son shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne"? Why then is Adonijah king?''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 14, 'Then while you are still speaking with the king, I also will come in after you and confirm your words."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 15, 'So Bathsheba went to the king in his chamber (now the king was very old, and Abishag the Shunammite was attending to the king).');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 16, 'Bathsheba bowed and paid homage to the king, and the king said, "What do you desire?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 17, 'She said to him, "My lord, you swore to your servant by the LORD your God, saying, ''Solomon your son shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 18, 'And now, behold, Adonijah is king, although you, my lord the king, do not know it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 19, 'He has sacrificed oxen, fattened cattle, and sheep in abundance, and has invited all the sons of the king, Abiathar the priest, and Joab the commander of the army, but Solomon your servant he has not invited.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 20, 'And now, my lord the king, the eyes of all Israel are on you, to tell them who shall sit on the throne of my lord the king after him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 21, 'Otherwise it will come to pass, when my lord the king sleeps with his fathers, that I and my son Solomon will be counted offenders."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 22, 'While she was still speaking with the king, Nathan the prophet came in.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 23, 'And they told the king, "Here is Nathan the prophet." And when he came in before the king, he bowed before the king, with his face to the ground.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 24, 'And Nathan said, "My lord the king, have you said, ''Adonijah shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne''?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 25, 'For he has gone down this day and has sacrificed oxen, fattened cattle, and sheep in abundance, and has invited all the king''s sons, the commanders of the army, and Abiathar the priest. And behold, they are eating and drinking before him, and saying, ''Long live King Adonijah!''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 26, 'But me, your servant, and Zadok the priest, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and your servant Solomon he has not invited.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 27, 'Has this thing been brought about by my lord the king and you have not told your servants who should sit on the throne of my lord the king after him?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 28, 'Then King David answered, "Call Bathsheba to me." So she came into the king''s presence and stood before the king.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 29, 'And the king swore, saying, "As the LORD lives, who has redeemed my soul out of every adversity,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 30, 'as I swore to you by the LORD, the God of Israel, saying, ''Solomon your son shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne in my place,'' even so will I do this day."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 31, 'Then Bathsheba bowed with her face to the ground and paid homage to the king and said, "May my lord King David live forever!"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 32, 'King David said, "Call to me Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada." So they came before the king.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 33, 'And the king said to them, "Take with you the servants of your lord and have Solomon my son ride on my own mule, and bring him down to Gihon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 34, 'And let Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet there anoint him king over Israel. Then blow the trumpet and say, ''Long live King Solomon!''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 35, 'You shall then come up after him, and he shall come and sit on my throne, for he shall be king in my place. And I have appointed him to be ruler over Israel and over Judah."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 36, 'And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada answered the king, "Amen! May the LORD, the God of my lord the king, say so.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 37, 'As the LORD has been with my lord the king, even so may he be with Solomon, and make his throne greater than the throne of my lord King David."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 38, 'So Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and the Cherethites and the Pelethites went down and had Solomon ride on King David''s mule and brought him to Gihon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 39, 'There Zadok the priest took the horn of oil from the tent and anointed Solomon. Then they blew the trumpet, and all the people said, "Long live King Solomon!"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 40, 'And all the people went up after him, playing on pipes, and rejoicing with great joy, so that the earth was split by their noise.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 41, 'Adonijah and all the guests who were with him heard it as they finished feasting. And when Joab heard the sound of the trumpet, he said, "What does this uproar in the city mean?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 42, 'While he was still speaking, behold, Jonathan the son of Abiathar the priest came. And Adonijah said, "Come in, for you are a worthy man and bring good news."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 43, 'Jonathan answered Adonijah, "No, for our lord King David has made Solomon king,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 44, 'and the king has sent with him Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and the Cherethites and the Pelethites. And they had him ride on the king''s mule.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 45, 'And Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet have anointed him king at Gihon, and they have gone up from there rejoicing, so that the city is in an uproar. This is the noise that you have heard.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 46, 'Solomon sits on the royal throne.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 47, 'Moreover, the king''s servants came to congratulate our lord King David, saying, ''May your God make the name of Solomon more famous than yours, and make his throne greater than your throne.'' And the king bowed himself on the bed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 48, 'And the king also said, ''Blessed be the LORD, the God of Israel, who has granted someone to sit on my throne this day, my own eyes seeing it.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 49, 'Then all the guests of Adonijah trembled and rose, and each went his own way.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 50, 'And Adonijah feared Solomon. So he arose and went and took hold of the horns of the altar.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 51, 'Then it was told Solomon, "Behold, Adonijah fears King Solomon, for behold, he has laid hold of the horns of the altar, saying, ''Let King Solomon swear to me first that he will not put his servant to death with the sword.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 52, 'And Solomon said, "If he will show himself a worthy man, not one of his hairs shall fall to the earth, but if wickedness is found in him, he shall die."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 1, 53, 'So King Solomon sent, and they brought him down from the altar. And he came and paid homage to King Solomon, and Solomon said to him, "Go to your house."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 1, 'When David''s time to die drew near, he commanded Solomon his son, saying,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 2, '"I am about to go the way of all the earth. Be strong, and show yourself a man,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 3, 'and keep the charge of the LORD your God, walking in his ways and keeping his statutes, his commandments, his rules, and his testimonies, as it is written in the Law of Moses, that you may prosper in all that you do and wherever you turn,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 4, 'that the LORD may establish his word that he spoke concerning me, saying, ''If your sons pay close attention to their way, to walk before me in faithfulness with all their heart and with all their soul, you shall not lack a man on the throne of Israel.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 5, '"Moreover, you also know what Joab the son of Zeruiah did to me, how he dealt with the two commanders of the armies of Israel, Abner the son of Ner, and Amasa the son of Jether, whom he killed, avenging in time of peace for blood that had been shed in war, and putting the blood of war on the belt around his waist and on the sandals on his feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 6, 'Act therefore according to your wisdom, but do not let his gray head go down to Sheol in peace.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 7, 'But deal loyally with the sons of Barzillai the Gileadite, and let them be among those who eat at your table, for with such loyalty they met me when I fled from Absalom your brother.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 8, 'And there is also with you Shimei the son of Gera, the Benjaminite from Bahurim, who cursed me with a grievous curse on the day when I went to Mahanaim. But when he came down to meet me at the Jordan, I swore to him by the LORD, saying, ''I will not put you to death with the sword.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 9, 'Now therefore do not hold him guiltless, for you are a wise man. You will know what you ought to do to him, and you shall bring his gray head down with blood to Sheol."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 10, 'Then David slept with his fathers and was buried in the city of David.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 11, 'And the time that David reigned over Israel was forty years. He reigned seven years in Hebron and thirty-three years in Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 12, 'So Solomon sat on the throne of David his father, and his kingdom was firmly established.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 13, 'Then Adonijah the son of Haggith came to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon. And she said, "Do you come peacefully?" He said, "Peacefully."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 14, 'Then he said, "I have something to say to you." She said, "Speak."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 15, 'He said, "You know that the kingdom was mine, and that all Israel fully expected me to reign. However, the kingdom has turned about and become my brother''s, for it was his from the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 16, 'And now I have one request to make of you; do not refuse me." She said to him, "Speak."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 17, 'And he said, "Please ask King Solomon- he will not refuse you- to give me Abishag the Shunammite as my wife."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 18, 'Bathsheba said, "Very well; I will speak for you to the king."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 19, 'So Bathsheba went to King Solomon to speak to him on behalf of Adonijah. And the king rose to meet her and bowed down to her. Then he sat on his throne and had a seat brought for the king''s mother, and she sat on his right.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 20, 'Then she said, "I have one small request to make of you; do not refuse me." And the king said to her, "Make your request, my mother, for I will not refuse you."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 21, 'She said, "Let Abishag the Shunammite be given to Adonijah your brother as his wife."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 22, 'King Solomon answered his mother, "And why do you ask Abishag the Shunammite for Adonijah? Ask for him the kingdom also, for he is my older brother, and on his side are Abiathar the priest and Joab the son of Zeruiah."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 23, 'Then King Solomon swore by the LORD, saying, "God do so to me and more also if this word does not cost Adonijah his life!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 24, 'Now therefore as the LORD lives, who has established me and placed me on the throne of David my father, and who has made me a house, as he promised, Adonijah shall be put to death this day."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 25, 'So King Solomon sent Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and he struck him down, and he died.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 26, 'And to Abiathar the priest the king said, "Go to Anathoth, to your estate, for you deserve death. But I will not at this time put you to death, because you carried the ark of the Lord GOD before David my father, and because you shared in all my father''s affliction."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 27, 'So Solomon expelled Abiathar from being priest to the LORD, thus fulfilling the word of the LORD that he had spoken concerning the house of Eli in Shiloh.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 28, 'When the news came to Joab- for Joab had supported Adonijah although he had not supported Absalom- Joab fled to the tent of the LORD and caught hold of the horns of the altar.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 29, 'And when it was told King Solomon, "Joab has fled to the tent of the LORD, and behold, he is beside the altar," Solomon sent Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, saying, "Go, strike him down."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 30, 'So Benaiah came to the tent of the LORD and said to him, "The king commands, ''Come out.''"But he said, "No, I will die here." Then Benaiah brought the king word again, saying, "Thus said Joab, and thus he answered me."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 31, 'The king replied to him, "Do as he has said, strike him down and bury him, and thus take away from me and from my father''s house the guilt for the blood that Joab shed without cause.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 32, 'The LORD will bring back his bloody deeds on his own head, because, without the knowledge of my father David, he attacked and killed with the sword two men more righteous and better than himself, Abner the son of Ner, commander of the army of Israel, and Amasa the son of Jether, commander of the army of Judah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 33, 'So shall their blood come back on the head of Joab and on the head of his descendants forever. But for David and for his descendants and for his house and for his throne there shall be peace from the LORD forevermore."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 34, 'Then Benaiah the son of Jehoiada went up and struck him down and put him to death. And he was buried in his own house in the wilderness.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 35, 'The king put Benaiah the son of Jehoiada over the army in place of Joab, and the king put Zadok the priest in the place of Abiathar.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 36, 'Then the king sent and summoned Shimei and said to him, "Build yourself a house in Jerusalem and dwell there, and do not go out from there to any place whatever.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 37, 'For on the day you go out and cross the brook Kidron, know for certain that you shall die. Your blood shall be on your own head."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 38, 'And Shimei said to the king, "What you say is good; as my lord the king has said, so will your servant do." So Shimei lived in Jerusalem many days.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 39, 'But it happened at the end of three years that two of Shimei''s servants ran away to Achish, son of Maacah, king of Gath. And when it was told Shimei, "Behold, your servants are in Gath,"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 40, 'Shimei arose and saddled a donkey and went to Gath to Achish to seek his servants. Shimei went and brought his servants from Gath.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 41, 'And when Solomon was told that Shimei had gone from Jerusalem to Gath and returned,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 42, 'the king sent and summoned Shimei and said to him, "Did I not make you swear by the LORD and solemnly warn you, saying, ''Know for certain that on the day you go out and go to any place whatever, you shall die''? And you said to me, ''What you say is good; I will obey.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 43, 'Why then have you not kept your oath to the LORD and the commandment with which I commanded you?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 44, 'The king also said to Shimei, "You know in your own heart all the harm that you did to David my father. So the LORD will bring back your harm on your own head.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 45, 'But King Solomon shall be blessed, and the throne of David shall be established before the LORD forever."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 2, 46, 'Then the king commanded Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and he went out and struck him down, and he died. So the kingdom was established in the hand of Solomon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 1, 'Solomon made a marriage alliance with Pharaoh king of Egypt. He took Pharaoh''s daughter and brought her into the city of David until he had finished building his own house and the house of the LORD and the wall around Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 2, 'The people were sacrificing at the high places, however, because no house had yet been built for the name of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 3, 'Solomon loved the LORD, walking in the statutes of David his father, only he sacrificed and made offerings at the high places.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 4, 'And the king went to Gibeon to sacrifice there, for that was the great high place. Solomon used to offer a thousand burnt offerings on that altar.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 5, 'At Gibeon the LORD appeared to Solomon in a dream by night, and God said, "Ask what I shall give you."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 6, 'And Solomon said, "You have shown great and steadfast love to your servant David my father, because he walked before you in faithfulness, in righteousness, and in uprightness of heart toward you. And you have kept for him this great and steadfast love and have given him a son to sit on his throne this day.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 7, 'And now, O LORD my God, you have made your servant king in place of David my father, although I am but a little child. I do not know how to go out or come in.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 8, 'And your servant is in the midst of your people whom you have chosen, a great people, too many to be numbered or counted for multitude.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 9, 'Give your servant therefore an understanding mind to govern your people, that I may discern between good and evil, for who is able to govern this your great people?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 10, 'It pleased the Lord that Solomon had asked this.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 11, 'And God said to him, "Because you have asked this, and have not asked for yourself long life or riches or the life of your enemies, but have asked for yourself understanding to discern what is right,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 12, 'behold, I now do according to your word. Behold, I give you a wise and discerning mind, so that none like you has been before you and none like you shall arise after you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 13, 'I give you also what you have not asked, both riches and honor, so that no other king shall compare with you, all your days.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 14, 'And if you will walk in my ways, keeping my statutes and my commandments, as your father David walked, then I will lengthen your days."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 15, 'And Solomon awoke, and behold, it was a dream. Then he came to Jerusalem and stood before the ark of the covenant of the LORD, and offered up burnt offerings and peace offerings, and made a feast for all his servants.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 16, 'Then two prostitutes came to the king and stood before him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 17, 'The one woman said, "Oh, my lord, this woman and I live in the same house, and I gave birth to a child while she was in the house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 18, 'Then on the third day after I gave birth, this woman also gave birth. And we were alone. There was no one else with us in the house; only we two were in the house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 19, 'And this woman''s son died in the night, because she lay on him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 20, 'And she arose at midnight and took my son from beside me, while your servant slept, and laid him at her breast, and laid her dead son at my breast.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 21, 'When I rose in the morning to nurse my child, behold, he was dead. But when I looked at him closely in the morning, behold, he was not the child that I had borne."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 22, 'But the other woman said, "No, the living child is mine, and the dead child is yours." The first said, "No, the dead child is yours, and the living child is mine." Thus they spoke before the king.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 23, 'Then the king said, "The one says, ''This is my son that is alive, and your son is dead''; and the other says, ''No; but your son is dead, and my son is the living one.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 24, 'And the king said, "Bring me a sword." So a sword was brought before the king.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 25, 'And the king said, "Divide the living child in two, and give half to the one and half to the other."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 26, 'Then the woman whose son was alive said to the king, because her heart yearned for her son, "Oh, my lord, give her the living child, and by no means put him to death." But the other said, "He shall be neither mine nor yours; divide him."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 27, 'Then the king answered and said, "Give the living child to the first woman, and by no means put him to death; she is his mother."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 3, 28, 'And all Israel heard of the judgment that the king had rendered, and they stood in awe of the king, because they perceived that the wisdom of God was in him to do justice.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 1, 'King Solomon was king over all Israel,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 2, 'and these were his high officials: Azariah the son of Zadok was the priest;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 3, 'Elihoreph and Ahijah the sons of Shisha were secretaries; Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was recorder;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 4, 'Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was in command of the army; Zadok and Abiathar were priests;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 5, 'Azariah the son of Nathan was over the officers; Zabud the son of Nathan was priest and king''s friend;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 6, 'Ahishar was in charge of the palace; and Adoniram the son of Abda was in charge of the forced labor.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 7, 'Solomon had twelve officers over all Israel, who provided food for the king and his household. Each man had to make provision for one month in the year.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 8, 'These were their names: Ben-hur, in the hill country of Ephraim;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 9, 'Ben-deker, in Makaz, Shaalbim, Beth-shemesh, and Elonbeth-hanan;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 10, 'Ben-hesed, in Arubboth (to him belonged Socoh and all the land of Hepher);');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 11, 'Ben-abinadab, in all Naphath-dor (he had Taphath the daughter of Solomon as his wife);');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 12, 'Baana the son of Ahilud, in Taanach, Megiddo, and all Beth-shean that is beside Zarethan below Jezreel, and from Beth-shean to Abel-meholah, as far as the other side of Jokmeam;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 13, 'Ben-geber, in Ramoth-gilead (he had the villages of Jair the son of Manasseh, which are in Gilead, and he had the region of Argob, which is in Bashan, sixty great cities with walls and bronze bars);');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 14, 'Ahinadab the son of Iddo, in Mahanaim;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 15, 'Ahimaaz, in Naphtali (he had taken Basemath the daughter of Solomon as his wife);');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 16, 'Baana the son of Hushai, in Asher and Bealoth;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 17, 'Jehoshaphat the son of Paruah, in Issachar;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 18, 'Shimei the son of Ela, in Benjamin;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 19, 'Geber the son of Uri, in the land of Gilead, the country of Sihon king of the Amorites and of Og king of Bashan. And there was one governor who was over the land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 20, 'Judah and Israel were as many as the sand by the sea. They ate and drank and were happy.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 21, 'Solomon ruled over all the kingdoms from the Euphrates to the land of the Philistines and to the border of Egypt. They brought tribute and served Solomon all the days of his life.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 22, 'Solomon''s provision for one day was thirty cors of fine flour and sixty cors of meal,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 23, 'ten fat oxen, and twenty pasture-fed cattle, a hundred sheep, besides deer, gazelles, roebucks, and fattened fowl.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 24, 'For he had dominion over all the region west of the Euphrates from Tiphsah to Gaza, over all the kings west of the Euphrates. And he had peace on all sides around him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 25, 'And Judah and Israel lived in safety, from Dan even to Beersheba, every man under his vine and under his fig tree, all the days of Solomon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 26, 'Solomon also had 40,000 stalls of horses for his chariots, and 12,000 horsemen.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 27, 'And those officers supplied provisions for King Solomon, and for all who came to King Solomon''s table, each one in his month. They let nothing be lacking.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 28, 'Barley also and straw for the horses and swift steeds they brought to the place where it was required, each according to his duty.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 29, 'And God gave Solomon wisdom and understanding beyond measure, and breadth of mind like the sand on the seashore,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 30, 'so that Solomon''s wisdom surpassed the wisdom of all the people of the east and all the wisdom of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 31, 'For he was wiser than all other men, wiser than Ethan the Ezrahite, and Heman, Calcol, and Darda, the sons of Mahol, and his fame was in all the surrounding nations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 32, 'He also spoke 3,000 proverbs, and his songs were 1,005.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 33, 'He spoke of trees, from the cedar that is in Lebanon to the hyssop that grows out of the wall. He spoke also of beasts, and of birds, and of reptiles, and of fish.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 4, 34, 'And people of all nations came to hear the wisdom of Solomon, and from all the kings of the earth, who had heard of his wisdom.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 1, 'Now Hiram king of Tyre sent his servants to Solomon when he heard that they had anointed him king in place of his father, for Hiram always loved David.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 2, 'And Solomon sent word to Hiram,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 3, '"You know that David my father could not build a house for the name of the LORD his God because of the warfare with which his enemies surrounded him, until the LORD put them under the soles of his feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 4, 'But now the LORD my God has given me rest on every side. There is neither adversary nor misfortune.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 5, 'And so I intend to build a house for the name of the LORD my God, as the LORD said to David my father, ''Your son, whom I will set on your throne in your place, shall build the house for my name.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 6, 'Now therefore command that cedars of Lebanon be cut for me. And my servants will join your servants, and I will pay you for your servants such wages as you set, for you know that there is no one among us who knows how to cut timber like the Sidonians."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 7, 'As soon as Hiram heard the words of Solomon, he rejoiced greatly and said, "Blessed be the LORD this day, who has given to David a wise son to be over this great people."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 8, 'And Hiram sent to Solomon, saying, "I have heard the message that you have sent to me. I am ready to do all you desire in the matter of cedar and cypress timber.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 9, 'My servants shall bring it down to the sea from Lebanon, and I will make it into rafts to go by sea to the place you direct. And I will have them broken up there, and you shall receive it. And you shall meet my wishes by providing food for my household."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 10, 'So Hiram supplied Solomon with all the timber of cedar and cypress that he desired,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 11, 'while Solomon gave Hiram 20,000 cors of wheat as food for his household, and 20,000 cors of beaten oil. Solomon gave this to Hiram year by year.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 12, 'And the LORD gave Solomon wisdom, as he promised him. And there was peace between Hiram and Solomon, and the two of them made a treaty.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 13, 'King Solomon drafted forced labor out of all Israel, and the draft numbered 30,000 men.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 14, 'And he sent them to Lebanon, 10,000 a month in shifts. They would be a month in Lebanon and two months at home. Adoniram was in charge of the draft.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 15, 'Solomon also had 70,000 burden-bearers and 80,000 stonecutters in the hill country,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 16, 'besides Solomon''s 3,300 chief officers who were over the work, who had charge of the people who carried on the work.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 17, 'At the king''s command they quarried out great, costly stones in order to lay the foundation of the house with dressed stones.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 5, 18, 'So Solomon''s builders and Hiram''s builders and the men of Gebal did the cutting and prepared the timber and the stone to build the house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 1, 'In the four hundred and eightieth year after the people of Israel came out of the land of Egypt, in the fourth year of Solomon''s reign over Israel, in the month of Ziv, which is the second month, he began to build the house of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 2, 'The house that King Solomon built for the LORD was sixty cubits long, twenty cubits wide, and thirty cubits high.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 3, 'The vestibule in front of the nave of the house was twenty cubits long, equal to the width of the house, and ten cubits deep in front of the house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 4, 'And he made for the house windows with recessed frames.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 5, 'He also built a structure against the wall of the house, running around the walls of the house, both the nave and the inner sanctuary. And he made side chambers all around.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 6, 'The lowest story was five cubits broad, the middle one was six cubits broad, and the third was seven cubits broad. For around the outside of the house he made offsets on the wall in order that the supporting beams should not be inserted into the walls of the house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 7, 'When the house was built, it was with stone prepared at the quarry, so that neither hammer nor axe nor any tool of iron was heard in the temple while it was being built.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 8, 'The entrance for the lowest story was on the south side of the house, and one went up by stairs to the middle story, and from the middle story to the third.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 9, 'So he built the house and finished it, and he made the ceiling of the house of beams and planks of cedar.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 10, 'He built the structure against the whole house, five cubits high, and it was joined to the house with timbers of cedar.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 11, 'Now the word of the LORD came to Solomon,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 12, '"Concerning this house that you are building, if you will walk in my statutes and obey my rules and keep all my commandments and walk in them, then I will establish my word with you, which I spoke to David your father.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 13, 'And I will dwell among the children of Israel and will not forsake my people Israel."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 14, 'So Solomon built the house and finished it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 15, 'He lined the walls of the house on the inside with boards of cedar. From the floor of the house to the walls of the ceiling, he covered them on the inside with wood, and he covered the floor of the house with boards of cypress.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 16, 'He built twenty cubits of the rear of the house with boards of cedar from the floor to the walls, and he built this within as an inner sanctuary, as the Most Holy Place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 17, 'The house, that is, the nave in front of the inner sanctuary, was forty cubits long.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 18, 'The cedar within the house was carved in the form of gourds and open flowers. All was cedar; no stone was seen.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 19, 'The inner sanctuary he prepared in the innermost part of the house, to set there the ark of the covenant of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 20, 'The inner sanctuary was twenty cubits long, twenty cubits wide, and twenty cubits high, and he overlaid it with pure gold. He also overlaid an altar of cedar.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 21, 'And Solomon overlaid the inside of the house with pure gold, and he drew chains of gold across, in front of the inner sanctuary, and overlaid it with gold.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 22, 'And he overlaid the whole house with gold, until all the house was finished. Also the whole altar that belonged to the inner sanctuary he overlaid with gold.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 23, 'In the inner sanctuary he made two cherubim of olivewood, each ten cubits high.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 24, 'Five cubits was the length of one wing of the cherub, and five cubits the length of the other wing of the cherub; it was ten cubits from the tip of one wing to the tip of the other.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 25, 'The other cherub also measured ten cubits; both cherubim had the same measure and the same form.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 26, 'The height of one cherub was ten cubits, and so was that of the other cherub.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 27, 'He put the cherubim in the innermost part of the house. And the wings of the cherubim were spread out so that a wing of one touched the one wall, and a wing of the other cherub touched the other wall; their other wings touched each other in the middle of the house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 28, 'And he overlaid the cherubim with gold.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 29, 'Around all the walls of the house he carved engraved figures of cherubim and palm trees and open flowers, in the inner and outer rooms.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 30, 'The floor of the house he overlaid with gold in the inner and outer rooms.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 31, 'For the entrance to the inner sanctuary he made doors of olivewood; the lintel and the doorposts were five-sided.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 32, 'He covered the two doors of olivewood with carvings of cherubim, palm trees, and open flowers. He overlaid them with gold and spread gold on the cherubim and on the palm trees.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 33, 'So also he made for the entrance to the nave doorposts of olivewood, in the form of a square,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 34, 'and two doors of cypress wood. The two leaves of the one door were folding, and the two leaves of the other door were folding.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 35, 'On them he carved cherubim and palm trees and open flowers, and he overlaid them with gold evenly applied on the carved work.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 36, 'He built the inner court with three courses of cut stone and one course of cedar beams.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 37, 'In the fourth year the foundation of the house of the LORD was laid, in the month of Ziv.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 6, 38, 'And in the eleventh year, in the month of Bul, which is the eighth month, the house was finished in all its parts, and according to all its specifications. He was seven years in building it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 1, 'Solomon was building his own house thirteen years, and he finished his entire house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 2, 'He built the House of the Forest of Lebanon. Its length was a hundred cubits and its breadth fifty cubits and its height thirty cubits, and it was built on four rows of cedar pillars, with cedar beams on the pillars.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 3, 'And it was covered with cedar above the chambers that were on the forty-five pillars, fifteen in each row.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 4, 'There were window frames in three rows, and window opposite window in three tiers.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 5, 'All the doorways and windows had square frames, and window was opposite window in three tiers.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 6, 'And he made the Hall of Pillars; its length was fifty cubits, and its breadth thirty cubits. There was a porch in front with pillars, and a canopy in front of them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 7, 'And he made the Hall of the Throne where he was to pronounce judgment, even the Hall of Judgment. It was finished with cedar from floor to rafters.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 8, 'His own house where he was to dwell, in the other court back of the hall, was of like workmanship. Solomon also made a house like this hall for Pharaoh''s daughter whom he had taken in marriage.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 9, 'All these were made of costly stones, cut according to measure, sawed with saws, back and front, even from the foundation to the coping, and from the outside to the great court.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 10, 'The foundation was of costly stones, huge stones, stones of eight and ten cubits.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 11, 'And above were costly stones, cut according to measurement, and cedar.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 12, 'The great court had three courses of cut stone all around, and a course of cedar beams; so had the inner court of the house of the LORD and the vestibule of the house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 13, 'And King Solomon sent and brought Hiram from Tyre.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 14, 'He was the son of a widow of the tribe of Naphtali, and his father was a man of Tyre, a worker in bronze. And he was full of wisdom, understanding, and skill for making any work in bronze. He came to King Solomon and did all his work.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 15, 'He cast two pillars of bronze. Eighteen cubits was the height of one pillar, and a line of twelve cubits measured its circumference. It was hollow, and its thickness was four fingers. The second pillar was the same.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 16, 'He also made two capitals of cast bronze to set on the tops of the pillars. The height of the one capital was five cubits, and the height of the other capital was five cubits.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 17, 'There were lattices of checker work with wreaths of chain work for the capitals on the tops of the pillars, a lattice for the one capital and a lattice for the other capital.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 18, 'Likewise he made pomegranates in two rows around the one latticework to cover the capital that was on the top of the pillar, and he did the same with the other capital.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 19, 'Now the capitals that were on the tops of the pillars in the vestibule were of lily-work, four cubits.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 20, 'The capitals were on the two pillars and also above the rounded projection which was beside the latticework. There were two hundred pomegranates in two rows all around, and so with the other capital.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 21, 'He set up the pillars at the vestibule of the temple. He set up the pillar on the south and called its name Jachin, and he set up the pillar on the north and called its name Boaz.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 22, 'And on the tops of the pillars was lily-work. Thus the work of the pillars was finished.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 23, 'Then he made the sea of cast metal. It was round, ten cubits from brim to brim, and five cubits high, and a line of thirty cubits measured its circumference.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 24, 'Under its brim were gourds, for ten cubits, compassing the sea all around. The gourds were in two rows, cast with it when it was cast.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 25, 'It stood on twelve oxen, three facing north, three facing west, three facing south, and three facing east. The sea was set on them, and all their rear parts were inward.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 26, 'Its thickness was a handbreadth, and its brim was made like the brim of a cup, like the flower of a lily. It held two thousand baths.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 27, 'He also made the ten stands of bronze. Each stand was four cubits long, four cubits wide, and three cubits high.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 28, 'This was the construction of the stands: they had panels, and the panels were set in the frames,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 29, 'and on the panels that were set in the frames were lions, oxen, and cherubim. On the frames, both above and below the lions and oxen, there were wreaths of beveled work.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 30, 'Moreover, each stand had four bronze wheels and axles of bronze, and at the four corners were supports for a basin. The supports were cast with wreaths at the side of each.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 31, 'Its opening was within a crown that projected upward one cubit. Its opening was round, as a pedestal is made, a cubit and a half deep. At its opening there were carvings, and its panels were square, not round.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 32, 'And the four wheels were underneath the panels. The axles of the wheels were of one piece with the stands, and the height of a wheel was a cubit and a half.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 33, 'The wheels were made like a chariot wheel; their axles, their rims, their spokes, and their hubs were all cast.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 34, 'There were four supports at the four corners of each stand. The supports were of one piece with the stands.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 35, 'And on the top of the stand there was a round band half a cubit high; and on the top of the stand its stays and its panels were of one piece with it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 36, 'And on the surfaces of its stays and on its panels, he carved cherubim, lions, and palm trees, according to the space of each, with wreaths all around.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 37, 'After this manner he made the ten stands. All of them were cast alike, of the same measure and the same form.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 38, 'And he made ten basins of bronze. Each basin held forty baths, each basin measured four cubits, and there was a basin for each of the ten stands.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 39, 'And he set the stands, five on the south side of the house, and five on the north side of the house. And he set the sea at the southeast corner of the house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 40, 'Hiram also made the pots, the shovels, and the basins. So Hiram finished all the work that he did for King Solomon on the house of the LORD:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 41, 'the two pillars, the two bowls of the capitals that were on the tops of the pillars, and the two latticeworks to cover the two bowls of the capitals that were on the tops of the pillars;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 42, 'and the four hundred pomegranates for the two latticeworks, two rows of pomegranates for each latticework, to cover the two bowls of the capitals that were on the pillars;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 43, 'the ten stands, and the ten basins on the stands;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 44, 'and the one sea, and the twelve oxen underneath the sea.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 45, 'Now the pots, the shovels, and the basins, all these vessels in the house of the LORD, which Hiram made for King Solomon, were of burnished bronze.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 46, 'In the plain of the Jordan the king cast them, in the clay ground between Succoth and Zarethan.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 47, 'And Solomon left all the vessels unweighed, because there were so many of them; the weight of the bronze was not ascertained.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 48, 'So Solomon made all the vessels that were in the house of the LORD: the golden altar, the golden table for the bread of the Presence,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 49, 'the lampstands of pure gold, five on the south side and five on the north, before the inner sanctuary; the flowers, the lamps, and the tongs, of gold;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 50, 'the cups, snuffers, basins, dishes for incense, and fire pans, of pure gold; and the sockets of gold, for the doors of the innermost part of the house, the Most Holy Place, and for the doors of the nave of the temple.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 7, 51, 'Thus all the work that King Solomon did on the house of the LORD was finished. And Solomon brought in the things that David his father had dedicated, the silver, the gold, and the vessels, and stored them in the treasuries of the house of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 1, 'Then Solomon assembled the elders of Israel and all the heads of the tribes, the leaders of the fathers'' houses of the people of Israel, before King Solomon in Jerusalem, to bring up the ark of the covenant of the LORD out of the city of David, which is Zion.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 2, 'And all the men of Israel assembled to King Solomon at the feast in the month Ethanim, which is the seventh month.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 3, 'And all the elders of Israel came, and the priests took up the ark.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 4, 'And they brought up the ark of the LORD, the tent of meeting, and all the holy vessels that were in the tent; the priests and the Levites brought them up.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 5, 'And King Solomon and all the congregation of Israel, who had assembled before him, were with him before the ark, sacrificing so many sheep and oxen that they could not be counted or numbered.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 6, 'Then the priests brought the ark of the covenant of the LORD to its place in the inner sanctuary of the house, in the Most Holy Place, underneath the wings of the cherubim.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 7, 'For the cherubim spread out their wings over the place of the ark, so that the cherubim overshadowed the ark and its poles.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 8, 'And the poles were so long that the ends of the poles were seen from the Holy Place before the inner sanctuary; but they could not be seen from outside. And they are there to this day.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 9, 'There was nothing in the ark except the two tablets of stone that Moses put there at Horeb, where the LORD made a covenant with the people of Israel, when they came out of the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 10, 'And when the priests came out of the Holy Place, a cloud filled the house of the LORD,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 11, 'so that the priests could not stand to minister because of the cloud, for the glory of the LORD filled the house of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 12, 'Then Solomon said, "The LORD has said that he would dwell in thick darkness.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 13, 'I have indeed built you an exalted house, a place for you to dwell in forever."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 14, 'Then the king turned around and blessed all the assembly of Israel, while all the assembly of Israel stood.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 15, 'And he said, "Blessed be the LORD, the God of Israel, who with his hand has fulfilled what he promised with his mouth to David my father, saying,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 16, '''Since the day that I brought my people Israel out of Egypt, I chose no city out of all the tribes of Israel in which to build a house, that my name might be there. But I chose David to be over my people Israel.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 17, 'Now it was in the heart of David my father to build a house for the name of the LORD, the God of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 18, 'But the LORD said to David my father, ''Whereas it was in your heart to build a house for my name, you did well that it was in your heart.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 19, 'Nevertheless, you shall not build the house, but your son who shall be born to you shall build the house for my name.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 20, 'Now the LORD has fulfilled his promise that he made. For I have risen in the place of David my father, and sit on the throne of Israel, as the LORD promised, and I have built the house for the name of the LORD, the God of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 21, 'And there I have provided a place for the ark, in which is the covenant of the LORD that he made with our fathers, when he brought them out of the land of Egypt."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 22, 'Then Solomon stood before the altar of the LORD in the presence of all the assembly of Israel and spread out his hands toward heaven,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 23, 'and said, "O LORD, God of Israel, there is no God like you, in heaven above or on earth beneath, keeping covenant and showing steadfast love to your servants who walk before you with all their heart,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 24, 'who have kept with your servant David my father what you declared to him. You spoke with your mouth, and with your hand have fulfilled it this day.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 25, 'Now therefore, O LORD, God of Israel, keep for your servant David my father what you have promised him, saying, ''You shall not lack a man to sit before me on the throne of Israel, if only your sons pay close attention to their way, to walk before me as you have walked before me.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 26, 'Now therefore, O God of Israel, let your word be confirmed, which you have spoken to your servant David my father.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 27, '"But will God indeed dwell on the earth? Behold, heaven and the highest heaven cannot contain you; how much less this house that I have built!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 28, 'Yet have regard to the prayer of your servant and to his plea, O LORD my God, listening to the cry and to the prayer that your servant prays before you this day,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 29, 'that your eyes may be open night and day toward this house, the place of which you have said, ''My name shall be there,'' that you may listen to the prayer that your servant offers toward this place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 30, 'And listen to the plea of your servant and of your people Israel, when they pray toward this place. And listen in heaven your dwelling place, and when you hear, forgive.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 31, '"If a man sins against his neighbor and is made to take an oath and comes and swears his oath before your altar in this house,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 32, 'then hear in heaven and act and judge your servants, condemning the guilty by bringing his conduct on his own head, and vindicating the righteous by rewarding him according to his righteousness.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 33, '"When your people Israel are defeated before the enemy because they have sinned against you, and if they turn again to you and acknowledge your name and pray and plead with you in this house,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 34, 'then hear in heaven and forgive the sin of your people Israel and bring them again to the land that you gave to their fathers.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 35, '"When heaven is shut up and there is no rain because they have sinned against you, if they pray toward this place and acknowledge your name and turn from their sin, when you afflict them,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 36, 'then hear in heaven and forgive the sin of your servants, your people Israel, when you teach them the good way in which they should walk, and grant rain upon your land, which you have given to your people as an inheritance.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 37, '"If there is famine in the land, if there is pestilence or blight or mildew or locust or caterpillar, if their enemy besieges them in the land at their gates, whatever plague, whatever sickness there is,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 38, 'whatever prayer, whatever plea is made by any man or by all your people Israel, each knowing the affliction of his own heart and stretching out his hands toward this house,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 39, 'then hear in heaven your dwelling place and forgive and act and render to each whose heart you know, according to all his ways ( for you, you only, know the hearts of all the children of mankind),');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 40, 'that they may fear you all the days that they live in the land that you gave to our fathers.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 41, '"Likewise, when a foreigner, who is not of your people Israel, comes from a far country for your name''s sake');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 42, '(for they shall hear of your great name and your mighty hand, and of your outstretched arm), when he comes and prays toward this house,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 43, 'hear in heaven your dwelling place and do according to all for which the foreigner calls to you, in order that all the peoples of the earth may know your name and fear you, as do your people Israel, and that they may know that this house that I have built is called by your name.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 44, '"If your people go out to battle against their enemy, by whatever way you shall send them, and they pray to the LORD toward the city that you have chosen and the house that I have built for your name,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 45, 'then hear in heaven their prayer and their plea, and maintain their cause.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 46, '"If they sin against you- for there is no one who does not sin- and you are angry with them and give them to an enemy, so that they are carried away captive to the land of the enemy, far off or near,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 47, 'yet if they turn their heart in the land to which they have been carried captive, and repent and plead with you in the land of their captors, saying, ''We have sinned and have acted perversely and wickedly,''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 48, 'if they repent with all their mind and with all their heart in the land of their enemies, who carried them captive, and pray to you toward their land, which you gave to their fathers, the city that you have chosen, and the house that I have built for your name,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 49, 'then hear in heaven your dwelling place their prayer and their plea, and maintain their cause');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 50, 'and forgive your people who have sinned against you, and all their transgressions that they have committed against you, and grant them compassion in the sight of those who carried them captive, that they may have compassion on them');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 51, '( for they are your people, and your heritage, which you brought out of Egypt, from the midst of the iron furnace).');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 52, 'Let your eyes be open to the plea of your servant and to the plea of your people Israel, giving ear to them whenever they call to you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 53, 'For you separated them from among all the peoples of the earth to be your heritage, as you declared through Moses your servant, when you brought our fathers out of Egypt, O Lord GOD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 54, 'Now as Solomon finished offering all this prayer and plea to the LORD, he arose from before the altar of the LORD, where he had knelt with hands outstretched toward heaven.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 55, 'And he stood and blessed all the assembly of Israel with a loud voice, saying,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 56, '"Blessed be the LORD who has given rest to his people Israel, according to all that he promised. Not one word has failed of all his good promise, which he spoke by Moses his servant.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 57, 'The LORD our God be with us, as he was with our fathers. May he not leave us or forsake us,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 58, 'that he may incline our hearts to him, to walk in all his ways and to keep his commandments, his statutes, and his rules, which he commanded our fathers.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 59, 'Let these words of mine, with which I have pleaded before the LORD, be near to the LORD our God day and night, and may he maintain the cause of his servant and the cause of his people Israel, as each day requires,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 60, 'that all the peoples of the earth may know that the LORD is God; there is no other.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 61, 'Let your heart therefore be wholly true to the LORD our God, walking in his statutes and keeping his commandments, as at this day."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 62, 'Then the king, and all Israel with him, offered sacrifice before the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 63, 'Solomon offered as peace offerings to the LORD 22,000 oxen and 120,000 sheep. So the king and all the people of Israel dedicated the house of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 64, 'The same day the king consecrated the middle of the court that was before the house of the LORD, for there he offered the burnt offering and the grain offering and the fat pieces of the peace offerings, because the bronze altar that was before the LORD was too small to receive the burnt offering and the grain offering and the fat pieces of the peace offerings.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 65, 'So Solomon held the feast at that time, and all Israel with him, a great assembly, from Lebo-hamath to the Brook of Egypt, before the LORD our God, seven days.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 8, 66, 'On the eighth day he sent the people away, and they blessed the king and went to their homes joyful and glad of heart for all the goodness that the LORD had shown to David his servant and to Israel his people.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 1, 'As soon as Solomon had finished building the house of the LORD and the king''s house and all that Solomon desired to build,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 2, 'the LORD appeared to Solomon a second time, as he had appeared to him at Gibeon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 3, 'And the LORD said to him, "I have heard your prayer and your plea, which you have made before me. I have consecrated this house that you have built, by putting my name there forever. My eyes and my heart will be there for all time.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 4, 'And as for you, if you will walk before me, as David your father walked, with integrity of heart and uprightness, doing according to all that I have commanded you, and keeping my statutes and my rules,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 5, 'then I will establish your royal throne over Israel forever, as I promised David your father, saying, ''You shall not lack a man on the throne of Israel.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 6, 'But if you turn aside from following me, you or your children, and do not keep my commandments and my statutes that I have set before you, but go and serve other gods and worship them,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 7, 'then I will cut off Israel from the land that I have given them, and the house that I have consecrated for my name I will cast out of my sight, and Israel will become a proverb and a byword among all peoples.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 8, 'And this house will become a heap of ruins. Everyone passing by it will be astonished and will hiss, and they will say, ''Why has the LORD done thus to this land and to this house?''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 9, 'Then they will say, ''Because they abandoned the LORD their God who brought their fathers out of the land of Egypt and laid hold on other gods and worshiped them and served them. Therefore the LORD has brought all this disaster on them.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 10, 'At the end of twenty years, in which Solomon had built the two houses, the house of the LORD and the king''s house,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 11, 'and Hiram king of Tyre had supplied Solomon with cedar and cypress timber and gold, as much as he desired, King Solomon gave to Hiram twenty cities in the land of Galilee.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 12, 'But when Hiram came from Tyre to see the cities that Solomon had given him, they did not please him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 13, 'Therefore he said, "What kind of cities are these that you have given me, my brother?" So they are called the land of Cabul to this day.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 14, 'Hiram had sent to the king 120 talents of gold.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 15, 'And this is the account of the forced labor that King Solomon drafted to build the house of the LORD and his own house and the Millo and the wall of Jerusalem and Hazor and Megiddo and Gezer');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 16, '(Pharaoh king of Egypt had gone up and captured Gezer and burned it with fire, and had killed the Canaanites who lived in the city, and had given it as dowry to his daughter, Solomon''s wife;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 17, 'so Solomon rebuilt Gezer) and Lower Beth-horon');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 18, 'and Baalath and Tamar in the wilderness, in the land of Judah,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 19, 'and all the store cities that Solomon had, and the cities for his chariots, and the cities for his horsemen, and whatever Solomon desired to build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon, and in all the land of his dominion.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 20, 'All the people who were left of the Amorites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, who were not of the people of Israel-');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 21, 'their descendants who were left after them in the land, whom the people of Israel were unable to devote to destruction- these Solomon drafted to be slaves, and so they are to this day.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 22, 'But of the people of Israel Solomon made no slaves. They were the soldiers, they were his officials, his commanders, his captains, his chariot commanders and his horsemen.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 23, 'These were the chief officers who were over Solomon''s work: 550 who had charge of the people who carried on the work.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 24, 'But Pharaoh''s daughter went up from the city of David to her own house that Solomon had built for her. Then he built the Millo.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 25, 'Three times a year Solomon used to offer up burnt offerings and peace offerings on the altar that he built to the LORD, making offerings with it before the LORD. So he finished the house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 26, 'King Solomon built a fleet of ships at Ezion-geber, which is near Eloth on the shore of the Red Sea, in the land of Edom.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 27, 'And Hiram sent with the fleet his servants, seamen who were familiar with the sea, together with the servants of Solomon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 9, 28, 'And they went to Ophir and brought from there gold, 420 talents, and they brought it to King Solomon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 1, 'Now when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon concerning the name of the LORD, she came to test him with hard questions.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 2, 'She came to Jerusalem with a very great retinue, with camels bearing spices and very much gold and precious stones. And when she came to Solomon, she told him all that was on her mind.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 3, 'And Solomon answered all her questions; there was nothing hidden from the king that he could not explain to her.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 4, 'And when the queen of Sheba had seen all the wisdom of Solomon, the house that he had built,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 5, 'the food of his table, the seating of his officials, and the attendance of his servants, their clothing, his cupbearers, and his burnt offerings that he offered at the house of the LORD, there was no more breath in her.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 6, 'And she said to the king, "The report was true that I heard in my own land of your words and of your wisdom,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 7, 'but I did not believe the reports until I came and my own eyes had seen it. And behold, the half was not told me. Your wisdom and prosperity surpass the report that I heard.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 8, 'Happy are your men! Happy are your servants, who continually stand before you and hear your wisdom!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 9, 'Blessed be the LORD your God, who has delighted in you and set you on the throne of Israel! Because the LORD loved Israel forever, he has made you king, that you may execute justice and righteousness."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 10, 'Then she gave the king 120 talents of gold, and a very great quantity of spices and precious stones. Never again came such an abundance of spices as these that the queen of Sheba gave to King Solomon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 11, 'Moreover, the fleet of Hiram, which brought gold from Ophir, brought from Ophir a very great amount of almug wood and precious stones.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 12, 'And the king made of the almug wood supports for the house of the LORD and for the king''s house, also lyres and harps for the singers. No such almug wood has come or been seen to this day.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 13, 'And King Solomon gave to the queen of Sheba all that she desired, whatever she asked besides what was given her by the bounty of King Solomon. So she turned and went back to her own land with her servants.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 14, 'Now the weight of gold that came to Solomon in one year was 666 talents of gold,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 15, 'besides that which came from the explorers and from the business of the merchants, and from all the kings of the west and from the governors of the land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 16, 'King Solomon made 200 large shields of beaten gold; 600 shekels of gold went into each shield.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 17, 'And he made 300 shields of beaten gold; three minas of gold went into each shield. And the king put them in the House of the Forest of Lebanon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 18, 'The king also made a great ivory throne and overlaid it with the finest gold.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 19, 'The throne had six steps, and at the back of the throne was a calf''s head, and on each side of the seat were armrests and two lions standing beside the armrests,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 20, 'while twelve lions stood there, one on each end of a step on the six steps. The like of it was never made in any kingdom.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 21, 'All King Solomon''s drinking vessels were of gold, and all the vessels of the House of the Forest of Lebanon were of pure gold. None were of silver; silver was not considered as anything in the days of Solomon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 22, 'For the king had a fleet of ships of Tarshish at sea with the fleet of Hiram. Once every three years the fleet of ships of Tarshish used to come bringing gold, silver, ivory, apes, and peacocks.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 23, 'Thus King Solomon excelled all the kings of the earth in riches and in wisdom.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 24, 'And the whole earth sought the presence of Solomon to hear his wisdom, which God had put into his mind.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 25, 'Every one of them brought his present, articles of silver and gold, garments, myrrh, spices, horses, and mules, so much year by year.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 26, 'And Solomon gathered together chariots and horsemen. He had 1,400 chariots and 12,000 horsemen, whom he stationed in the chariot cities and with the king in Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 27, 'And the king made silver as common in Jerusalem as stone, and he made cedar as plentiful as the sycamore of the Shephelah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 28, 'And Solomon''s import of horses was from Egypt and Kue, and the king''s traders received them from Kue at a price.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 10, 29, 'A chariot could be imported from Egypt for 600 shekels of silver and a horse for 150, and so through the king''s traders they were exported to all the kings of the Hittites and the kings of Syria.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 1, 'Now King Solomon loved many foreign women, along with the daughter of Pharaoh: Moabite, Ammonite, Edomite, Sidonian, and Hittite women,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 2, 'from the nations concerning which the LORD had said to the people of Israel, "You shall not enter into marriage with them, neither shall they with you, for surely they will turn away your heart after their gods." Solomon clung to these in love.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 3, 'He had 700 wives, princesses, and 300 concubines. And his wives turned away his heart.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 4, 'For when Solomon was old his wives turned away his heart after other gods, and his heart was not wholly true to the LORD his God, as was the heart of David his father.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 5, 'For Solomon went after Ashtoreth the goddess of the Sidonians, and after Milcom the abomination of the Ammonites.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 6, 'So Solomon did what was evil in the sight of the LORD and did not wholly follow the LORD, as David his father had done.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 7, 'Then Solomon built a high place for Chemosh the abomination of Moab, and for Molech the abomination of the Ammonites, on the mountain east of Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 8, 'And so he did for all his foreign wives, who made offerings and sacrificed to their gods.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 9, 'And the LORD was angry with Solomon, because his heart had turned away from the LORD, the God of Israel, who had appeared to him twice');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 10, 'and had commanded him concerning this thing, that he should not go after other gods. But he did not keep what the LORD commanded.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 11, 'Therefore the LORD said to Solomon, "Since this has been your practice and you have not kept my covenant and my statutes that I have commanded you, I will surely tear the kingdom from you and will give it to your servant.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 12, 'Yet for the sake of David your father I will not do it in your days, but I will tear it out of the hand of your son.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 13, 'However, I will not tear away all the kingdom, but I will give one tribe to your son, for the sake of David my servant and for the sake of Jerusalem that I have chosen."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 14, 'And the LORD raised up an adversary against Solomon, Hadad the Edomite. He was of the royal house in Edom.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 15, 'For when David was in Edom, and Joab the commander of the army went up to bury the slain, he struck down every male in Edom');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 16, '(for Joab and all Israel remained there six months, until he had cut off every male in Edom).');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 17, 'But Hadad fled to Egypt, together with certain Edomites of his father''s servants, Hadad still being a little child.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 18, 'They set out from Midian and came to Paran and took men with them from Paran and came to Egypt, to Pharaoh king of Egypt, who gave him a house and assigned him an allowance of food and gave him land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 19, 'And Hadad found great favor in the sight of Pharaoh, so that he gave him in marriage the sister of his own wife, the sister of Tahpenes the queen.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 20, 'And the sister of Tahpenes bore him Genubath his son, whom Tahpenes weaned in Pharaoh''s house. And Genubath was in Pharaoh''s house among the sons of Pharaoh.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 21, 'But when Hadad heard in Egypt that David slept with his fathers and that Joab the commander of the army was dead, Hadad said to Pharaoh, "Let me depart, that I may go to my own country."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 22, 'But Pharaoh said to him, "What have you lacked with me that you are now seeking to go to your own country?" And he said to him, "Only let me depart."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 23, 'God also raised up as an adversary to him, Rezon the son of Eliada, who had fled from his master Hadadezer king of Zobah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 24, 'And he gathered men about him and became leader of a marauding band, after the killing by David. And they went to Damascus and lived there and made him king in Damascus.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 25, 'He was an adversary of Israel all the days of Solomon, doing harm as Hadad did. And he loathed Israel and reigned over Syria.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 26, 'Jeroboam the son of Nebat, an Ephraimite of Zeredah, a servant of Solomon, whose mother''s name was Zeruah, a widow, also lifted up his hand against the king.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 27, 'And this was the reason why he lifted up his hand against the king. Solomon built the Millo, and closed up the breach of the city of David his father.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 28, 'The man Jeroboam was very able, and when Solomon saw that the young man was industrious he gave him charge over all the forced labor of the house of Joseph.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 29, 'And at that time, when Jeroboam went out of Jerusalem, the prophet Ahijah the Shilonite found him on the road. Now Ahijah had dressed himself in a new garment, and the two of them were alone in the open country.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 30, 'Then Ahijah laid hold of the new garment that was on him, and tore it into twelve pieces.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 31, 'And he said to Jeroboam, "Take for yourself ten pieces, for thus says the LORD, the God of Israel, ''Behold, I am about to tear the kingdom from the hand of Solomon and will give you ten tribes');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 32, '(but he shall have one tribe, for the sake of my servant David and for the sake of Jerusalem, the city that I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel),');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 33, 'because they have forsaken me and worshiped Ashtoreth the goddess of the Sidonians, Chemosh the god of Moab, and Milcom the god of the Ammonites, and they have not walked in my ways, doing what is right in my sight and keeping my statutes and my rules, as David his father did.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 34, 'Nevertheless, I will not take the whole kingdom out of his hand, but I will make him ruler all the days of his life, for the sake of David my servant whom I chose, who kept my commandments and my statutes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 35, 'But I will take the kingdom out of his son''s hand and will give it to you, ten tribes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 36, 'Yet to his son I will give one tribe, that David my servant may always have a lamp before me in Jerusalem, the city where I have chosen to put my name.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 37, 'And I will take you, and you shall reign over all that your soul desires, and you shall be king over Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 38, 'And if you will listen to all that I command you, and will walk in my ways, and do what is right in my eyes by keeping my statutes and my commandments, as David my servant did, I will be with you and will build you a sure house, as I built for David, and I will give Israel to you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 39, 'And I will afflict the offspring of David because of this, but not forever.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 40, 'Solomon sought therefore to kill Jeroboam. But Jeroboam arose and fled into Egypt, to Shishak king of Egypt, and was in Egypt until the death of Solomon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 41, 'Now the rest of the acts of Solomon, and all that he did, and his wisdom, are they not written in the Book of the Acts of Solomon?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 42, 'And the time that Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel was forty years.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 11, 43, 'And Solomon slept with his fathers and was buried in the city of David his father. And Rehoboam his son reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 1, 'Rehoboam went to Shechem, for all Israel had come to Shechem to make him king.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 2, 'And as soon as Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard of it (for he was still in Egypt, where he had fled from King Solomon), then Jeroboam returned from Egypt.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 3, 'And they sent and called him, and Jeroboam and all the assembly of Israel came and said to Rehoboam,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 4, '"Your father made our yoke heavy. Now therefore lighten the hard service of your father and his heavy yoke on us, and we will serve you."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 5, 'He said to them, "Go away for three days, then come again to me." So the people went away.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 6, 'Then King Rehoboam took counsel with the old men, who had stood before Solomon his father while he was yet alive, saying, "How do you advise me to answer this people?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 7, 'And they said to him, "If you will be a servant to this people today and serve them, and speak good words to them when you answer them, then they will be your servants forever."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 8, 'But he abandoned the counsel that the old men gave him and took counsel with the young men who had grown up with him and stood before him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 9, 'And he said to them, "What do you advise that we answer this people who have said to me, ''Lighten the yoke that your father put on us''?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 10, 'And the young men who had grown up with him said to him, "Thus shall you speak to this people who said to you, ''Your father made our yoke heavy, but you lighten it for us,'' thus shall you say to them, ''My little finger is thicker than my father''s thighs.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 11, 'And now, whereas my father laid on you a heavy yoke, I will add to your yoke. My father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with scorpions.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 12, 'So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam the third day, as the king said, "Come to me again the third day."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 13, 'And the king answered the people harshly, and forsaking the counsel that the old men had given him,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 14, 'he spoke to them according to the counsel of the young men, saying, "My father made your yoke heavy, but I will add to your yoke. My father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with scorpions."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 15, 'So the king did not listen to the people, for it was a turn of affairs brought about by the LORD that he might fulfill his word, which the LORD spoke by Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 16, 'And when all Israel saw that the king did not listen to them, the people answered the king, "What portion do we have in David? We have no inheritance in the son of Jesse. To your tents, O Israel! Look now to your own house, David." So Israel went to their tents.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 17, 'But Rehoboam reigned over the people of Israel who lived in the cities of Judah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 18, 'Then King Rehoboam sent Adoram, who was taskmaster over the forced labor, and all Israel stoned him to death with stones. And King Rehoboam hurried to mount his chariot to flee to Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 19, 'So Israel has been in rebellion against the house of David to this day.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 20, 'And when all Israel heard that Jeroboam had returned, they sent and called him to the assembly and made him king over all Israel. There was none that followed the house of David but the tribe of Judah only.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 21, 'When Rehoboam came to Jerusalem, he assembled all the house of Judah and the tribe of Benjamin, 180,000 chosen warriors, to fight against the house of Israel, to restore the kingdom to Rehoboam the son of Solomon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 22, 'But the word of God came to Shemaiah the man of God:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 23, '"Say to Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and to all the house of Judah and Benjamin, and to the rest of the people,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 24, '''Thus says the LORD, You shall not go up or fight against your relatives the people of Israel. Every man return to his home, for this thing is from me.''"So they listened to the word of the LORD and went home again, according to the word of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 25, 'Then Jeroboam built Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim and lived there. And he went out from there and built Penuel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 26, 'And Jeroboam said in his heart, "Now the kingdom will turn back to the house of David.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 27, 'If this people go up to offer sacrifices in the temple of the LORD at Jerusalem, then the heart of this people will turn again to their lord, to Rehoboam king of Judah, and they will kill me and return to Rehoboam king of Judah."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 28, 'So the king took counsel and made two calves of gold. And he said to the people, "You have gone up to Jerusalem long enough. Behold your gods, O Israel, who brought you up out of the land of Egypt."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 29, 'And he set one in Bethel, and the other he put in Dan.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 30, 'Then this thing became a sin, for the people went as far as Dan to be before one.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 31, 'He also made temples on high places and appointed priests from among all the people, who were not of the Levites.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 32, 'And Jeroboam appointed a feast on the fifteenth day of the eighth month like the feast that was in Judah, and he offered sacrifices on the altar. So he did in Bethel, sacrificing to the calves that he made. And he placed in Bethel the priests of the high places that he had made.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 12, 33, 'He went up to the altar that he had made in Bethel on the fifteenth day in the eighth month, in the month that he had devised from his own heart. And he instituted a feast for the people of Israel and went up to the altar to make offerings.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 1, 'And behold, a man of God came out of Judah by the word of the LORD to Bethel. Jeroboam was standing by the altar to make offerings.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 2, 'And the man cried against the altar by the word of the LORD and said, "O altar, altar, thus says the LORD: ''Behold, a son shall be born to the house of David, Josiah by name, and he shall sacrifice on you the priests of the high places who make offerings on you, and human bones shall be burned on you.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 3, 'And he gave a sign the same day, saying, "This is the sign that the LORD has spoken: ''Behold, the altar shall be torn down, and the ashes that are on it shall be poured out.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 4, 'And when the king heard the saying of the man of God, which he cried against the altar at Bethel, Jeroboam stretched out his hand from the altar, saying, "Seize him." And his hand, which he stretched out against him, dried up, so that he could not draw it back to himself.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 5, 'The altar also was torn down, and the ashes poured out from the altar, according to the sign that the man of God had given by the word of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 6, 'And the king said to the man of God, "Entreat now the favor of the LORD your God, and pray for me, that my hand may be restored to me." And the man of God entreated the LORD, and the king''s hand was restored to him and became as it was before.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 7, 'And the king said to the man of God, "Come home with me, and refresh yourself, and I will give you a reward."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 8, 'And the man of God said to the king, "If you give me half your house, I will not go in with you. And I will not eat bread or drink water in this place,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 9, 'for so was it commanded me by the word of the LORD, saying, ''You shall neither eat bread nor drink water nor return by the way that you came.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 10, 'So he went another way and did not return by the way that he came to Bethel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 11, 'Now an old prophet lived in Bethel. And his sons came and told him all that the man of God had done that day in Bethel. They also told to their father the words that he had spoken to the king.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 12, 'And their father said to them, "Which way did he go?" And his sons showed him the way that the man of God who came from Judah had gone.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 13, 'And he said to his sons, "Saddle the donkey for me." So they saddled the donkey for him and he mounted it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 14, 'And he went after the man of God and found him sitting under an oak. And he said to him, "Are you the man of God who came from Judah?" And he said, "I am."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 15, 'Then he said to him, "Come home with me and eat bread."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 16, 'And he said, "I may not return with you, or go in with you, neither will I eat bread nor drink water with you in this place,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 17, 'for it was said to me by the word of the LORD, ''You shall neither eat bread nor drink water there, nor return by the way that you came.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 18, 'And he said to him, "I also am a prophet as you are, and an angel spoke to me by the word of the LORD, saying, ''Bring him back with you into your house that he may eat bread and drink water.''"But he lied to him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 19, 'So he went back with him and ate bread in his house and drank water.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 20, 'And as they sat at the table, the word of the LORD came to the prophet who had brought him back.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 21, 'And he cried to the man of God who came from Judah, "Thus says the LORD, ''Because you have disobeyed the word of the LORD and have not kept the command that the LORD your God commanded you,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 22, 'but have come back and have eaten bread and drunk water in the place of which he said to you, "Eat no bread and drink no water," your body shall not come to the tomb of your fathers.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 23, 'And after he had eaten bread and drunk, he saddled the donkey for the prophet whom he had brought back.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 24, 'And as he went away a lion met him on the road and killed him. And his body was thrown in the road, and the donkey stood beside it; the lion also stood beside the body.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 25, 'And behold, men passed by and saw the body thrown in the road and the lion standing by the body. And they came and told it in the city where the old prophet lived.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 26, 'And when the prophet who had brought him back from the way heard of it, he said, "It is the man of God who disobeyed the word of the LORD; therefore the LORD has given him to the lion, which has torn him and killed him, according to the word that the LORD spoke to him."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 27, 'And he said to his sons, "Saddle the donkey for me." And they saddled it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 28, 'And he went and found his body thrown in the road, and the donkey and the lion standing beside the body. The lion had not eaten the body or torn the donkey.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 29, 'And the prophet took up the body of the man of God and laid it on the donkey and brought it back to the city to mourn and to bury him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 30, 'And he laid the body in his own grave. And they mourned over him, saying, "Alas, my brother!"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 31, 'And after he had buried him, he said to his sons, "When I die, bury me in the grave in which the man of God is buried; lay my bones beside his bones.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 32, 'For the saying that he called out by the word of the LORD against the altar in Bethel and against all the houses of the high places that are in the cities of Samaria shall surely come to pass."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 33, 'After this thing Jeroboam did not turn from his evil way, but made priests for the high places again from among all the people. Any who would, he ordained to be priests of the high places.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 13, 34, 'And this thing became sin to the house of Jeroboam, so as to cut it off and to destroy it from the face of the earth.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 1, 'At that time Abijah the son of Jeroboam fell sick.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 2, 'And Jeroboam said to his wife, "Arise, and disguise yourself, that it not be known that you are the wife of Jeroboam, and go to Shiloh. Behold, Ahijah the prophet is there, who said of me that I should be king over this people.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 3, 'Take with you ten loaves, some cakes, and a jar of honey, and go to him. He will tell you what shall happen to the child."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 4, 'Jeroboam''s wife did so. She arose and went to Shiloh and came to the house of Ahijah. Now Ahijah could not see, for his eyes were dim because of his age.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 5, 'And the LORD said to Ahijah, "Behold, the wife of Jeroboam is coming to inquire of you concerning her son, for he is sick. Thus and thus shall you say to her." When she came, she pretended to be another woman.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 6, 'But when Ahijah heard the sound of her feet, as she came in at the door, he said, "Come in, wife of Jeroboam. Why do you pretend to be another? For I am charged with unbearable news for you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 7, 'Go, tell Jeroboam, ''Thus says the LORD, the God of Israel: "Because I exalted you from among the people and made you leader over my people Israel');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 8, 'and tore the kingdom away from the house of David and gave it to you, and yet you have not been like my servant David, who kept my commandments and followed me with all his heart, doing only that which was right in my eyes,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 9, 'but you have done evil above all who were before you and have gone and made for yourself other gods and metal images, provoking me to anger, and have cast me behind your back,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 10, 'therefore behold, I will bring harm upon the house of Jeroboam and will cut off from Jeroboam every male, both bond and free in Israel, and will burn up the house of Jeroboam, as a man burns up dung until it is all gone.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 11, 'Anyone belonging to Jeroboam who dies in the city the dogs shall eat, and anyone who dies in the open country the birds of the heavens shall eat, for the LORD has spoken it."''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 12, 'Arise therefore, go to your house. When your feet enter the city, the child shall die.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 13, 'And all Israel shall mourn for him and bury him, for he only of Jeroboam shall come to the grave, because in him there is found something pleasing to the LORD, the God of Israel, in the house of Jeroboam.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 14, 'Moreover, the LORD will raise up for himself a king over Israel who shall cut off the house of Jeroboam today. And henceforth,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 15, 'the LORD will strike Israel as a reed is shaken in the water, and root up Israel out of this good land that he gave to their fathers and scatter them beyond the Euphrates, because they have made their Asherim, provoking the LORD to anger.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 16, 'And he will give Israel up because of the sins of Jeroboam, which he sinned and made Israel to sin."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 17, 'Then Jeroboam''s wife arose and departed and came to Tirzah. And as she came to the threshold of the house, the child died.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 18, 'And all Israel buried him and mourned for him, according to the word of the LORD, which he spoke by his servant Ahijah the prophet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 19, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jeroboam, how he warred and how he reigned, behold, they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 20, 'And the time that Jeroboam reigned was twenty-two years. And he slept with his fathers, and Nadab his son reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 21, 'Now Rehoboam the son of Solomon reigned in Judah. Rehoboam was forty-one years old when he began to reign, and he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem, the city that the LORD had chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, to put his name there. His mother''s name was Naamah the Ammonite.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 22, 'And Judah did what was evil in the sight of the LORD, and they provoked him to jealousy with their sins that they committed, more than all that their fathers had done.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 23, 'For they also built for themselves high places and pillars and Asherim on every high hill and under every green tree,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 24, 'and there were also male cult prostitutes in the land. They did according to all the abominations of the nations that the LORD drove out before the people of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 25, 'In the fifth year of King Rehoboam, Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 26, 'He took away the treasures of the house of the LORD and the treasures of the king''s house. He took away everything. He also took away all the shields of gold that Solomon had made,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 27, 'and King Rehoboam made in their place shields of bronze, and committed them to the hands of the officers of the guard, who kept the door of the king''s house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 28, 'And as often as the king went into the house of the LORD, the guard carried them and brought them back to the guardroom.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 29, 'Now the rest of the acts of Rehoboam and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 30, 'And there was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam continually.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 14, 31, 'And Rehoboam slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the city of David. His mother''s name was Naamah the Ammonite. And Abijam his son reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 1, 'Now in the eighteenth year of King Jeroboam the son of Nebat, Abijam began to reign over Judah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 2, 'He reigned for three years in Jerusalem. His mother''s name was Maacah the daughter of Abishalom.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 3, 'And he walked in all the sins that his father did before him, and his heart was not wholly true to the LORD his God, as the heart of David his father.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 4, 'Nevertheless, for David''s sake the LORD his God gave him a lamp in Jerusalem, setting up his son after him, and establishing Jerusalem,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 5, 'because David did what was right in the eyes of the LORD and did not turn aside from anything that he commanded him all the days of his life, except in the matter of Uriah the Hittite.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 6, 'Now there was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all the days of his life.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 7, 'The rest of the acts of Abijam and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? And there was war between Abijam and Jeroboam.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 8, 'And Abijam slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city of David. And Asa his son reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 9, 'In the twentieth year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Asa began to reign over Judah,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 10, 'and he reigned forty-one years in Jerusalem. His mother''s name was Maacah the daughter of Abishalom.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 11, 'And Asa did what was right in the eyes of the LORD, as David his father had done.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 12, 'He put away the male cult prostitutes out of the land and removed all the idols that his fathers had made.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 13, 'He also removed Maacah his mother from being queen mother because she had made an abominable image for Asherah. And Asa cut down her image and burned it at the brook Kidron.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 14, 'But the high places were not taken away. Nevertheless, the heart of Asa was wholly true to the LORD all his days.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 15, 'And he brought into the house of the LORD the sacred gifts of his father and his own sacred gifts, silver, and gold, and vessels.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 16, 'And there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 17, 'Baasha king of Israel went up against Judah and built Ramah, that he might permit no one to go out or come in to Asa king of Judah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 18, 'Then Asa took all the silver and the gold that were left in the treasures of the house of the LORD and the treasures of the king''s house and gave them into the hands of his servants. And King Asa sent them to Ben-hadad the son of Tabrimmon, the son of Hezion, king of Syria, who lived in Damascus, saying,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 19, '"Let there be a covenant between me and you, as there was between my father and your father. Behold, I am sending to you a present of silver and gold. Go, break your covenant with Baasha king of Israel, that he may withdraw from me."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 20, 'And Ben-hadad listened to King Asa and sent the commanders of his armies against the cities of Israel and conquered Ijon, Dan, Abel-beth-maacah, and all Chinneroth, with all the land of Naphtali.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 21, 'And when Baasha heard of it, he stopped building Ramah, and he lived in Tirzah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 22, 'Then King Asa made a proclamation to all Judah, none was exempt, and they carried away the stones of Ramah and its timber, with which Baasha had been building, and with them King Asa built Geba of Benjamin and Mizpah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 23, 'Now the rest of all the acts of Asa, all his might, and all that he did, and the cities that he built, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? But in his old age he was diseased in his feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 24, 'And Asa slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the city of David his father, and Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 25, 'Nadab the son of Jeroboam began to reign over Israel in the second year of Asa king of Judah, and he reigned over Israel two years.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 26, 'He did what was evil in the sight of the LORD and walked in the way of his father, and in his sin which he made Israel to sin.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 27, 'Baasha the son of Ahijah, of the house of Issachar, conspired against him. And Baasha struck him down at Gibbethon, which belonged to the Philistines, for Nadab and all Israel were laying siege to Gibbethon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 28, 'So Baasha killed him in the third year of Asa king of Judah and reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 29, 'And as soon as he was king, he killed all the house of Jeroboam. He left to the house of Jeroboam not one that breathed, until he had destroyed it, according to the word of the LORD that he spoke by his servant Ahijah the Shilonite.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 30, 'It was for the sins of Jeroboam that he sinned and that he made Israel to sin, and because of the anger to which he provoked the LORD, the God of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 31, 'Now the rest of the acts of Nadab and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 32, 'And there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 33, 'In the third year of Asa king of Judah, Baasha the son of Ahijah began to reign over all Israel at Tirzah, and he reigned twenty-four years.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 15, 34, 'He did what was evil in the sight of the LORD and walked in the way of Jeroboam and in his sin which he made Israel to sin.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 1, 'And the word of the LORD came to Jehu the son of Hanani against Baasha, saying,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 2, '"Since I exalted you out of the dust and made you leader over my people Israel, and you have walked in the way of Jeroboam and have made my people Israel to sin, provoking me to anger with their sins,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 3, 'behold, I will utterly sweep away Baasha and his house, and I will make your house like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 4, 'Anyone belonging to Baasha who dies in the city the dogs shall eat, and anyone of his who dies in the field the birds of the heavens shall eat."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 5, 'Now the rest of the acts of Baasha and what he did, and his might, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 6, 'And Baasha slept with his fathers and was buried at Tirzah, and Elah his son reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 7, 'Moreover, the word of the LORD came by the prophet Jehu the son of Hanani against Baasha and his house, both because of all the evil that he did in the sight of the LORD, provoking him to anger with the work of his hands, in being like the house of Jeroboam, and also because he destroyed it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 8, 'In the twenty-sixth year of Asa king of Judah, Elah the son of Baasha began to reign over Israel in Tirzah, and he reigned two years.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 9, 'But his servant Zimri, commander of half his chariots, conspired against him. When he was at Tirzah, drinking himself drunk in the house of Arza, who was over the household in Tirzah,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 10, 'Zimri came in and struck him down and killed him, in the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, and reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 11, 'When he began to reign, as soon as he had seated himself on his throne, he struck down all the house of Baasha. He did not leave him a single male of his relatives or his friends.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 12, 'Thus Zimri destroyed all the house of Baasha, according to the word of the LORD, which he spoke against Baasha by Jehu the prophet,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 13, 'for all the sins of Baasha and the sins of Elah his son, which they sinned and which they made Israel to sin, provoking the LORD God of Israel to anger with their idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 14, 'Now the rest of the acts of Elah and all that he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 15, 'In the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, Zimri reigned seven days in Tirzah. Now the troops were encamped against Gibbethon, which belonged to the Philistines,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 16, 'and the troops who were encamped heard it said, "Zimri has conspired, and he has killed the king." Therefore all Israel made Omri, the commander of the army, king over Israel that day in the camp.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 17, 'So Omri went up from Gibbethon, and all Israel with him, and they besieged Tirzah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 18, 'And when Zimri saw that the city was taken, he went into the citadel of the king''s house and burned the king''s house over him with fire and died,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 19, 'because of his sins that he committed, doing evil in the sight of the LORD, walking in the way of Jeroboam, and for his sin which he committed, making Israel to sin.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 20, 'Now the rest of the acts of Zimri, and the conspiracy that he made, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 21, 'Then the people of Israel were divided into two parts. Half of the people followed Tibni the son of Ginath, to make him king, and half followed Omri.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 22, 'But the people who followed Omri overcame the people who followed Tibni the son of Ginath. So Tibni died, and Omri became king.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 23, 'In the thirty-first year of Asa king of Judah, Omri began to reign over Israel, and he reigned for twelve years; six years he reigned in Tirzah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 24, 'He bought the hill of Samaria from Shemer for two talents of silver, and he fortified the hill and called the name of the city that he built Samaria, after the name of Shemer, the owner of the hill.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 25, 'Omri did what was evil in the sight of the LORD, and did more evil than all who were before him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 26, 'For he walked in all the way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and in the sins that he made Israel to sin, provoking the LORD, the God of Israel, to anger by their idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 27, 'Now the rest of the acts of Omri that he did, and the might that he showed, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 28, 'And Omri slept with his fathers and was buried in Samaria, and Ahab his son reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 29, 'In the thirty-eighth year of Asa king of Judah, Ahab the son of Omri began to reign over Israel, and Ahab the son of Omri reigned over Israel in Samaria twenty-two years.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 30, 'And Ahab the son of Omri did evil in the sight of the LORD, more than all who were before him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 31, 'And as if it had been a light thing for him to walk in the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, he took for his wife Jezebel the daughter of Ethbaal king of the Sidonians, and went and served Baal and worshiped him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 32, 'He erected an altar for Baal in the house of Baal, which he built in Samaria.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 33, 'And Ahab made an Asherah. Ahab did more to provoke the LORD, the God of Israel, to anger than all the kings of Israel who were before him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 16, 34, 'In his days Hiel of Bethel built Jericho. He laid its foundation at the cost of Abiram his firstborn, and set up its gates at the cost of his youngest son Segub, according to the word of the LORD, which he spoke by Joshua the son of Nun.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 1, 'Now Elijah the Tishbite, of Tishbe in Gilead, said to Ahab, "As the LORD the God of Israel lives, before whom I stand, there shall be neither dew nor rain these years, except by my word."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 2, 'And the word of the LORD came to him,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 3, '"Depart from here and turn eastward and hide yourself by the brook Cherith, which is east of the Jordan.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 4, 'You shall drink from the brook, and I have commanded the ravens to feed you there."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 5, 'So he went and did according to the word of the LORD. He went and lived by the brook Cherith that is east of the Jordan.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 6, 'And the ravens brought him bread and meat in the morning, and bread and meat in the evening, and he drank from the brook.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 7, 'And after a while the brook dried up, because there was no rain in the land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 8, 'Then the word of the LORD came to him,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 9, '"Arise, go to Zarephath, which belongs to Sidon, and dwell there. Behold, I have commanded a widow there to feed you."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 10, 'So he arose and went to Zarephath. And when he came to the gate of the city, behold, a widow was there gathering sticks. And he called to her and said, "Bring me a little water in a vessel, that I may drink."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 11, 'And as she was going to bring it, he called to her and said, "Bring me a morsel of bread in your hand."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 12, 'And she said, "As the LORD your God lives, I have nothing baked, only a handful of flour in a jar and a little oil in a jug. And now I am gathering a couple of sticks that I may go in and prepare it for myself and my son, that we may eat it and die."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 13, 'And Elijah said to her, "Do not fear; go and do as you have said. But first make me a little cake of it and bring it to me, and afterward make something for yourself and your son.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 14, 'For thus says the LORD the God of Israel, ''The jar of flour shall not be spent, and the jug of oil shall not be empty, until the day that the LORD sends rain upon the earth.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 15, 'And she went and did as Elijah said. And she and he and her household ate for many days.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 16, 'The jar of flour was not spent, neither did the jug of oil become empty, according to the word of the LORD that he spoke by Elijah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 17, 'After this the son of the woman, the mistress of the house, became ill. And his illness was so severe that there was no breath left in him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 18, 'And she said to Elijah, "What have you against me, O man of God? You have come to me to bring my sin to remembrance and to cause the death of my son!"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 19, 'And he said to her, "Give me your son." And he took him from her arms and carried him up into the upper chamber where he lodged, and laid him on his own bed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 20, 'And he cried to the LORD, "O LORD my God, have you brought calamity even upon the widow with whom I sojourn, by killing her son?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 21, 'Then he stretched himself upon the child three times and cried to the LORD, "O LORD my God, let this child''s life come into him again."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 22, 'And the LORD listened to the voice of Elijah. And the life of the child came into him again, and he revived.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 23, 'And Elijah took the child and brought him down from the upper chamber into the house and delivered him to his mother. And Elijah said, "See, your son lives."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 17, 24, 'And the woman said to Elijah, "Now I know that you are a man of God, and that the word of the LORD in your mouth is truth."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 1, 'After many days the word of the LORD came to Elijah, in the third year, saying, "Go, show yourself to Ahab, and I will send rain upon the earth."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 2, 'So Elijah went to show himself to Ahab. Now the famine was severe in Samaria.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 3, 'And Ahab called Obadiah, who was over the household. (Now Obadiah feared the LORD greatly,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 4, 'and when Jezebel cut off the prophets of the LORD, Obadiah took a hundred prophets and hid them by fifties in a cave and fed them with bread and water.)');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 5, 'And Ahab said to Obadiah, "Go through the land to all the springs of water and to all the valleys. Perhaps we may find grass and save the horses and mules alive, and not lose some of the animals."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 6, 'So they divided the land between them to pass through it. Ahab went in one direction by himself, and Obadiah went in another direction by himself.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 7, 'And as Obadiah was on the way, behold, Elijah met him. And Obadiah recognized him and fell on his face and said, "Is it you, my lord Elijah?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 8, 'And he answered him, "It is I. Go, tell your lord, ''Behold, Elijah is here.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 9, 'And he said, "How have I sinned, that you would give your servant into the hand of Ahab, to kill me?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 10, 'As the LORD your God lives, there is no nation or kingdom where my lord has not sent to seek you. And when they would say, ''He is not here,'' he would take an oath of the kingdom or nation, that they had not found you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 11, 'And now you say, ''Go, tell your lord, "Behold, Elijah is here."''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 12, 'And as soon as I have gone from you, the Spirit of the LORD will carry you I know not where. And so, when I come and tell Ahab and he cannot find you, he will kill me, although I your servant have feared the LORD from my youth.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 13, 'Has it not been told my lord what I did when Jezebel killed the prophets of the LORD, how I hid a hundred men of the LORD''s prophets by fifties in a cave and fed them with bread and water?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 14, 'And now you say, ''Go, tell your lord, "Behold, Elijah is here"''; and he will kill me."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 15, 'And Elijah said, "As the LORD of hosts lives, before whom I stand, I will surely show myself to him today."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 16, 'So Obadiah went to meet Ahab, and told him. And Ahab went to meet Elijah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 17, 'When Ahab saw Elijah, Ahab said to him, "Is it you, you troubler of Israel?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 18, 'And he answered, "I have not troubled Israel, but you have, and your father''s house, because you have abandoned the commandments of the LORD and followed the Baals.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 19, 'Now therefore send and gather all Israel to me at Mount Carmel, and the 450 prophets of Baal and the 400 prophets of Asherah, who eat at Jezebel''s table."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 20, 'So Ahab sent to all the people of Israel and gathered the prophets together at Mount Carmel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 21, 'And Elijah came near to all the people and said, "How long will you go limping between two different opinions? If the LORD is God, follow him; but if Baal, then follow him." And the people did not answer him a word.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 22, 'Then Elijah said to the people, "I, even I only, am left a prophet of the LORD, but Baal''s prophets are 450 men.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 23, 'Let two bulls be given to us, and let them choose one bull for themselves and cut it in pieces and lay it on the wood, but put no fire to it. And I will prepare the other bull and lay it on the wood and put no fire to it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 24, 'And you call upon the name of your god, and I will call upon the name of the LORD, and the God who answers by fire, he is God." And all the people answered, "It is well spoken."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 25, 'Then Elijah said to the prophets of Baal, "Choose for yourselves one bull and prepare it first, for you are many, and call upon the name of your god, but put no fire to it."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 26, 'And they took the bull that was given them, and they prepared it and called upon the name of Baal from morning until noon, saying, "O Baal, answer us!" But there was no voice, and no one answered. And they limped around the altar that they had made.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 27, 'And at noon Elijah mocked them, saying, "Cry aloud, for he is a god. Either he is musing, or he is relieving himself, or he is on a journey, or perhaps he is asleep and must be awakened."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 28, 'And they cried aloud and cut themselves after their custom with swords and lances, until the blood gushed out upon them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 29, 'And as midday passed, they raved on until the time of the offering of the oblation, but there was no voice. No one answered; no one paid attention.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 30, 'Then Elijah said to all the people, "Come near to me." And all the people came near to him. And he repaired the altar of the LORD that had been thrown down.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 31, 'Elijah took twelve stones, according to the number of the tribes of the sons of Jacob, to whom the word of the LORD came, saying, "Israel shall be your name,"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 32, 'and with the stones he built an altar in the name of the LORD. And he made a trench about the altar, as great as would contain two seahs of seed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 33, 'And he put the wood in order and cut the bull in pieces and laid it on the wood. And he said, "Fill four jars with water and pour it on the burnt offering and on the wood."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 34, 'And he said, "Do it a second time." And they did it a second time. And he said, "Do it a third time." And they did it a third time.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 35, 'And the water ran around the altar and filled the trench also with water.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 36, 'And at the time of the offering of the oblation, Elijah the prophet came near and said, "O LORD, God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, let it be known this day that you are God in Israel, and that I am your servant, and that I have done all these things at your word.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 37, 'Answer me, O LORD, answer me, that this people may know that you, O LORD, are God, and that you have turned their hearts back."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 38, 'Then the fire of the LORD fell and consumed the burnt offering and the wood and the stones and the dust, and licked up the water that was in the trench.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 39, 'And when all the people saw it, they fell on their faces and said, "The LORD, he is God; the LORD, he is God."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 40, 'And Elijah said to them, "Seize the prophets of Baal; let not one of them escape." And they seized them. And Elijah brought them down to the brook Kishon and slaughtered them there.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 41, 'And Elijah said to Ahab, "Go up, eat and drink, for there is a sound of the rushing of rain."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 42, 'So Ahab went up to eat and to drink. And Elijah went up to the top of Mount Carmel. And he bowed himself down on the earth and put his face between his knees.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 43, 'And he said to his servant, "Go up now, look toward the sea." And he went up and looked and said, "There is nothing." And he said, "Go again," seven times.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 44, 'And at the seventh time he said, "Behold, a little cloud like a man''s hand is rising from the sea." And he said, "Go up, say to Ahab, ''Prepare your chariot and go down, lest the rain stop you.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 45, 'And in a little while the heavens grew black with clouds and wind, and there was a great rain. And Ahab rode and went to Jezreel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 18, 46, 'And the hand of the LORD was on Elijah, and he gathered up his garment and ran before Ahab to the entrance of Jezreel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 1, 'Ahab told Jezebel all that Elijah had done, and how he had killed all the prophets with the sword.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 2, 'Then Jezebel sent a messenger to Elijah, saying, "So may the gods do to me and more also, if I do not make your life as the life of one of them by this time tomorrow."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 3, 'Then he was afraid, and he arose and ran for his life and came to Beersheba, which belongs to Judah, and left his servant there.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 4, 'But he himself went a day''s journey into the wilderness and came and sat down under a broom tree. And he asked that he might die, saying, "It is enough; now, O LORD, take away my life, for I am no better than my fathers."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 5, 'And he lay down and slept under a broom tree. And behold, an angel touched him and said to him, "Arise and eat."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 6, 'And he looked, and behold, there was at his head a cake baked on hot stones and a jar of water. And he ate and drank and lay down again.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 7, 'And the angel of the LORD came again a second time and touched him and said, "Arise and eat, for the journey is too great for you."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 8, 'And he arose and ate and drank, and went in the strength of that food forty days and forty nights to Horeb, the mount of God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 9, 'There he came to a cave and lodged in it. And behold, the word of the LORD came to him, and he said to him, "What are you doing here, Elijah?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 10, 'He said, "I have been very jealous for the LORD, the God of hosts. For the people of Israel have forsaken your covenant, thrown down your altars, and killed your prophets with the sword, and I, even I only, am left, and they seek my life, to take it away."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 11, 'And he said, "Go out and stand on the mount before the LORD." And behold, the LORD passed by, and a great and strong wind tore the mountains and broke in pieces the rocks before the LORD, but the LORD was not in the wind. And after the wind an earthquake, but the LORD was not in the earthquake.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 12, 'And after the earthquake a fire, but the LORD was not in the fire. And after the fire the sound of a low whisper.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 13, 'And when Elijah heard it, he wrapped his face in his cloak and went out and stood at the entrance of the cave. And behold, there came a voice to him and said, "What are you doing here, Elijah?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 14, 'He said, "I have been very jealous for the LORD, the God of hosts. For the people of Israel have forsaken your covenant, thrown down your altars, and killed your prophets with the sword, and I, even I only, am left, and they seek my life, to take it away."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 15, 'And the LORD said to him, "Go, return on your way to the wilderness of Damascus. And when you arrive, you shall anoint Hazael to be king over Syria.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 16, 'And Jehu the son of Nimshi you shall anoint to be king over Israel, and Elisha the son of Shaphat of Abel-meholah you shall anoint to be prophet in your place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 17, 'And the one who escapes from the sword of Hazael shall Jehu put to death, and the one who escapes from the sword of Jehu shall Elisha put to death.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 18, 'Yet I will leave seven thousand in Israel, all the knees that have not bowed to Baal, and every mouth that has not kissed him."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 19, 'So he departed from there and found Elisha the son of Shaphat, who was plowing with twelve yoke of oxen in front of him, and he was with the twelfth. Elijah passed by him and cast his cloak upon him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 20, 'And he left the oxen and ran after Elijah and said, "Let me kiss my father and my mother, and then I will follow you." And he said to him, "Go back again, for what have I done to you?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 19, 21, 'And he returned from following him and took the yoke of oxen and sacrificed them and boiled their flesh with the yokes of the oxen and gave it to the people, and they ate. Then he arose and went after Elijah and assisted him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 1, 'Ben-hadad the king of Syria gathered all his army together. Thirty-two kings were with him, and horses and chariots. And he went up and closed in on Samaria and fought against it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 2, 'And he sent messengers into the city to Ahab king of Israel and said to him, "Thus says Ben-hadad:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 3, '''Your silver and your gold are mine; your best wives and children also are mine.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 4, 'And the king of Israel answered, "As you say, my lord, O king, I am yours, and all that I have."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 5, 'The messengers came again and said, "Thus says Ben-hadad: ''I sent to you, saying, "Deliver to me your silver and your gold, your wives and your children."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 6, 'Nevertheless I will send my servants to you tomorrow about this time, and they shall search your house and the houses of your servants and lay hands on whatever pleases you and take it away.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 7, 'Then the king of Israel called all the elders of the land and said, "Mark, now, and see how this man is seeking trouble, for he sent to me for my wives and my children, and for my silver and my gold, and I did not refuse him."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 8, 'And all the elders and all the people said to him, "Do not listen or consent."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 9, 'So he said to the messengers of Ben-hadad, "Tell my lord the king, ''All that you first demanded of your servant I will do, but this thing I cannot do.''"And the messengers departed and brought him word again.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 10, 'Ben-hadad sent to him and said, "The gods do so to me and more also, if the dust of Samaria shall suffice for handfuls for all the people who follow me."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 11, 'And the king of Israel answered, "Tell him, ''Let not him who straps on his armor boast himself like he who takes it off.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 12, 'When Ben-hadad heard this message as he was drinking with the kings in the booths, he said to his men, "Take your positions." And they took their positions against the city.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 13, 'And behold, a prophet came near to Ahab king of Israel and said, "Thus says the LORD, Have you seen all this great multitude? Behold, I will give it into your hand this day, and you shall know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 14, 'And Ahab said, "By whom?" He said, "Thus says the LORD, By the servants of the governors of the districts." Then he said, "Who shall begin the battle?" He answered, "You."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 15, 'Then he mustered the servants of the governors of the districts, and they were 232. And after them he mustered all the people of Israel, seven thousand.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 16, 'And they went out at noon, while Ben-hadad was drinking himself drunk in the booths, he and the thirty-two kings who helped him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 17, 'The servants of the governors of the districts went out first. And Ben-hadad sent out scouts, and they reported to him, "Men are coming out from Samaria."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 18, 'He said, "If they have come out for peace, take them alive. Or if they have come out for war, take them alive."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 19, 'So these went out of the city, the servants of the governors of the districts and the army that followed them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 20, 'And each struck down his man. The Syrians fled, and Israel pursued them, but Ben-hadad king of Syria escaped on a horse with horsemen.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 21, 'And the king of Israel went out and struck the horses and chariots, and struck the Syrians with a great blow.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 22, 'Then the prophet came near to the king of Israel and said to him, "Come, strengthen yourself, and consider well what you have to do, for in the spring the king of Syria will come up against you."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 23, 'And the servants of the king of Syria said to him, "Their gods are gods of the hills, and so they were stronger than we. But let us fight against them in the plain, and surely we shall be stronger than they.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 24, 'And do this: remove the kings, each from his post, and put commanders in their places,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 25, 'and muster an army like the army that you have lost, horse for horse, and chariot for chariot. Then we will fight against them in the plain, and surely we shall be stronger than they." And he listened to their voice and did so.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 26, 'In the spring, Ben-hadad mustered the Syrians and went up to Aphek to fight against Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 27, 'And the people of Israel were mustered and were provisioned and went against them. The people of Israel encamped before them like two little flocks of goats, but the Syrians filled the country.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 28, 'And a man of God came near and said to the king of Israel, "Thus says the LORD, ''Because the Syrians have said, "The LORD is a god of the hills but he is not a god of the valleys," therefore I will give all this great multitude into your hand, and you shall know that I am the LORD.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 29, 'And they encamped opposite one another seven days. Then on the seventh day the battle was joined. And the people of Israel struck down of the Syrians 100,000 foot soldiers in one day.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 30, 'And the rest fled into the city of Aphek, and the wall fell upon 27,000 men who were left. Ben-hadad also fled and entered an inner chamber in the city.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 31, 'And his servants said to him, "Behold now, we have heard that the kings of the house of Israel are merciful kings. Let us put sackcloth around our waists and ropes on our heads and go out to the king of Israel. Perhaps he will spare your life."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 32, 'So they tied sackcloth around their waists and put ropes on their heads and went to the king of Israel and said, "Your servant Ben-hadad says, ''Please, let me live.''"And he said, "Does he still live? He is my brother."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 33, 'Now the men were watching for a sign, and they quickly took it up from him and said, "Yes, your brother Ben-hadad." Then he said, "Go and bring him." Then Ben-hadad came out to him, and he caused him to come up into the chariot.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 34, 'And Ben-hadad said to him, "The cities that my father took from your father I will restore, and you may establish bazaars for yourself in Damascus, as my father did in Samaria." And Ahab said, "I will let you go on these terms." So he made a covenant with him and let him go.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 35, 'And a certain man of the sons of the prophets said to his fellow at the command of the LORD, "Strike me, please." But the man refused to strike him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 36, 'Then he said to him, "Because you have not obeyed the voice of the LORD, behold, as soon as you have gone from me, a lion shall strike you down." And as soon as he had departed from him, a lion met him and struck him down.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 37, 'Then he found another man and said, "Strike me, please." And the man struck him- struck him and wounded him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 38, 'So the prophet departed and waited for the king by the way, disguising himself with a bandage over his eyes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 39, 'And as the king passed, he cried to the king and said, "Your servant went out into the midst of the battle, and behold, a soldier turned and brought a man to me and said, ''Guard this man; if by any means he is missing, your life shall be for his life, or else you shall pay a talent of silver.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 40, 'And as your servant was busy here and there, he was gone." The king of Israel said to him, "So shall your judgment be; you yourself have decided it."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 41, 'Then he hurried to take the bandage away from his eyes, and the king of Israel recognized him as one of the prophets.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 42, 'And he said to him, "Thus says the LORD, ''Because you have let go out of your hand the man whom I had devoted to destruction, therefore your life shall be for his life, and your people for his people.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 20, 43, 'And the king of Israel went to his house vexed and sullen and came to Samaria.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 1, 'Now Naboth the Jezreelite had a vineyard in Jezreel, beside the palace of Ahab king of Samaria.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 2, 'And after this Ahab said to Naboth, "Give me your vineyard, that I may have it for a vegetable garden, because it is near my house, and I will give you a better vineyard for it; or, if it seems good to you, I will give you its value in money."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 3, 'But Naboth said to Ahab, "The LORD forbid that I should give you the inheritance of my fathers."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 4, 'And Ahab went into his house vexed and sullen because of what Naboth the Jezreelite had said to him, for he had said, "I will not give you the inheritance of my fathers." And he lay down on his bed and turned away his face and would eat no food.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 5, 'But Jezebel his wife came to him and said to him, "Why is your spirit so vexed that you eat no food?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 6, 'And he said to her, "Because I spoke to Naboth the Jezreelite and said to him, ''Give me your vineyard for money, or else, if it please you, I will give you another vineyard for it.'' And he answered, ''I will not give you my vineyard.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 7, 'And Jezebel his wife said to him, "Do you now govern Israel? Arise and eat bread and let your heart be cheerful; I will give you the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 8, 'So she wrote letters in Ahab''s name and sealed them with his seal, and she sent the letters to the elders and the leaders who lived with Naboth in his city.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 9, 'And she wrote in the letters, "Proclaim a fast, and set Naboth at the head of the people.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 10, 'And set two worthless men opposite him, and let them bring a charge against him, saying, ''You have cursed God and the king.'' Then take him out and stone him to death."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 11, 'And the men of his city, the elders and the leaders who lived in his city, did as Jezebel had sent word to them. As it was written in the letters that she had sent to them,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 12, 'they proclaimed a fast and set Naboth at the head of the people.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 13, 'And the two worthless men came in and sat opposite him. And the worthless men brought a charge against Naboth in the presence of the people, saying, "Naboth cursed God and the king." So they took him outside the city and stoned him to death with stones.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 14, 'Then they sent to Jezebel, saying, "Naboth has been stoned; he is dead."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 15, 'As soon as Jezebel heard that Naboth had been stoned and was dead, Jezebel said to Ahab, "Arise, take possession of the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, which he refused to give you for money, for Naboth is not alive, but dead."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 16, 'And as soon as Ahab heard that Naboth was dead, Ahab arose to go down to the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, to take possession of it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 17, 'Then the word of the LORD came to Elijah the Tishbite, saying,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 18, '"Arise, go down to meet Ahab king of Israel, who is in Samaria; behold, he is in the vineyard of Naboth, where he has gone to take possession.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 19, 'And you shall say to him, ''Thus says the LORD, "Have you killed and also taken possession?"''And you shall say to him, ''Thus says the LORD: "In the place where dogs licked up the blood of Naboth shall dogs lick your own blood."''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 20, 'Ahab said to Elijah, "Have you found me, O my enemy?" He answered, "I have found you, because you have sold yourself to do what is evil in the sight of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 21, 'Behold, I will bring disaster upon you. I will utterly burn you up, and will cut off from Ahab every male, bond or free, in Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 22, 'And I will make your house like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah, for the anger to which you have provoked me, and because you have made Israel to sin.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 23, 'And of Jezebel the LORD also said, ''The dogs shall eat Jezebel within the walls of Jezreel.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 24, 'Anyone belonging to Ahab who dies in the city the dogs shall eat, and anyone of his who dies in the open country the birds of the heavens shall eat."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 25, '( There was none who sold himself to do what was evil in the sight of the LORD like Ahab, whom Jezebel his wife incited.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 26, 'He acted very abominably in going after idols, as the Amorites had done, whom the LORD cast out before the people of Israel.)');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 27, 'And when Ahab heard those words, he tore his clothes and put sackcloth on his flesh and fasted and lay in sackcloth and went about dejectedly.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 28, 'And the word of the LORD came to Elijah the Tishbite, saying,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 21, 29, '"Have you seen how Ahab has humbled himself before me? Because he has humbled himself before me, I will not bring the disaster in his days; but in his son''s days I will bring the disaster upon his house."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 1, 'For three years Syria and Israel continued without war.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 2, 'But in the third year Jehoshaphat the king of Judah came down to the king of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 3, 'And the king of Israel said to his servants, "Do you know that Ramoth-gilead belongs to us, and we keep quiet and do not take it out of the hand of the king of Syria?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 4, 'And he said to Jehoshaphat, "Will you go with me to battle at Ramoth-gilead?" And Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, "I am as you are, my people as your people, my horses as your horses."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 5, 'And Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, "Inquire first for the word of the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 6, 'Then the king of Israel gathered the prophets together, about four hundred men, and said to them, "Shall I go to battle against Ramoth-gilead, or shall I refrain?" And they said, "Go up, for the Lord will give it into the hand of the king."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 7, 'But Jehoshaphat said, "Is there not here another prophet of the LORD of whom we may inquire?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 8, 'And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, "There is yet one man by whom we may inquire of the LORD, Micaiah the son of Imlah, but I hate him, for he never prophesies good concerning me, but evil." And Jehoshaphat said, "Let not the king say so."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 9, 'Then the king of Israel summoned an officer and said, "Bring quickly Micaiah the son of Imlah."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 10, 'Now the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah were sitting on their thrones, arrayed in their robes, at the threshing floor at the entrance of the gate of Samaria, and all the prophets were prophesying before them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 11, 'And Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah made for himself horns of iron and said, "Thus says the LORD, ''With these you shall push the Syrians until they are destroyed.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 12, 'And all the prophets prophesied so and said, "Go up to Ramoth-gilead and triumph; the LORD will give it into the hand of the king."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 13, 'And the messenger who went to summon Micaiah said to him, "Behold, the words of the prophets with one accord are favorable to the king. Let your word be like the word of one of them, and speak favorably."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 14, 'But Micaiah said, "As the LORD lives, what the LORD says to me, that I will speak."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 15, 'And when he had come to the king, the king said to him, "Micaiah, shall we go to Ramoth-gilead to battle, or shall we refrain?" And he answered him, "Go up and triumph; the LORD will give it into the hand of the king."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 16, 'But the king said to him, "How many times shall I make you swear that you speak to me nothing but the truth in the name of the LORD?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 17, 'And he said, "I saw all Israel scattered on the mountains, as sheep that have no shepherd. And the LORD said, ''These have no master; let each return to his home in peace.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 18, 'And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, "Did I not tell you that he would not prophesy good concerning me, but evil?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 19, 'And Micaiah said, "Therefore hear the word of the LORD: I saw the LORD sitting on his throne, and all the host of heaven standing beside him on his right hand and on his left;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 20, 'and the LORD said, ''Who will entice Ahab, that he may go up and fall at Ramoth-gilead?'' And one said one thing, and another said another.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 21, 'Then a spirit came forward and stood before the LORD, saying, ''I will entice him.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 22, 'And the LORD said to him, ''By what means?'' And he said, ''I will go out, and will be a lying spirit in the mouth of all his prophets.'' And he said, ''You are to entice him, and you shall succeed; go out and do so.''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 23, 'Now therefore behold, the LORD has put a lying spirit in the mouth of all these your prophets; the LORD has declared disaster for you."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 24, 'Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah came near and struck Micaiah on the cheek and said, "How did the Spirit of the LORD go from me to speak to you?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 25, 'And Micaiah said, "Behold, you shall see on that day when you go into an inner chamber to hide yourself."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 26, 'And the king of Israel said, "Seize Micaiah, and take him back to Amon the governor of the city and to Joash the king''s son,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 27, 'and say, ''Thus says the king, "Put this fellow in prison and feed him meager rations of bread and water, until I come in peace."''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 28, 'And Micaiah said, "If you return in peace, the LORD has not spoken by me." And he said, "Hear, all you peoples!"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 29, 'So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah went up to Ramoth-gilead.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 30, 'And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, "I will disguise myself and go into battle, but you wear your robes." And the king of Israel disguised himself and went into battle.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 31, 'Now the king of Syria had commanded the thirty-two captains of his chariots, "Fight with neither small nor great, but only with the king of Israel."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 32, 'And when the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat, they said, "It is surely the king of Israel." So they turned to fight against him. And Jehoshaphat cried out.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 33, 'And when the captains of the chariots saw that it was not the king of Israel, they turned back from pursuing him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 34, 'But a certain man drew his bow at random and struck the king of Israel between the scale armor and the breastplate. Therefore he said to the driver of his chariot, "Turn around and carry me out of the battle, for I am wounded."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 35, 'And the battle continued that day, and the king was propped up in his chariot facing the Syrians, until at evening he died. And the blood of the wound flowed into the bottom of the chariot.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 36, 'And about sunset a cry went through the army, "Every man to his city, and every man to his country!"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 37, 'So the king died, and was brought to Samaria. And they buried the king in Samaria.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 38, 'And they washed the chariot by the pool of Samaria, and the dogs licked up his blood, and the prostitutes washed themselves in it, according to the word of the LORD that he had spoken.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 39, 'Now the rest of the acts of Ahab and all that he did, and the ivory house that he built and all the cities that he built, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 40, 'So Ahab slept with his fathers, and Ahaziah his son reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 41, 'Jehoshaphat the son of Asa began to reign over Judah in the fourth year of Ahab king of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 42, 'Jehoshaphat was thirty-five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned twenty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother''s name was Azubah the daughter of Shilhi.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 43, 'He walked in all the way of Asa his father. He did not turn aside from it, doing what was right in the sight of the LORD. Yet the high places were not taken away, and the people still sacrificed and made offerings on the high places.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 44, 'Jehoshaphat also made peace with the king of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 45, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, and his might that he showed, and how he warred, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 46, 'And from the land he exterminated the remnant of the male cult prostitutes who remained in the days of his father Asa.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 47, 'There was no king in Edom; a deputy was king.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 48, 'Jehoshaphat made ships of Tarshish to go to Ophir for gold, but they did not go, for the ships were wrecked at Ezion-geber.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 49, 'Then Ahaziah the son of Ahab said to Jehoshaphat, "Let my servants go with your servants in the ships," but Jehoshaphat was not willing.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 50, 'And Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in the city of David his father, and Jehoram his son reigned in his place.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 51, 'Ahaziah the son of Ahab began to reign over Israel in Samaria in the seventeenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and he reigned two years over Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 52, 'He did what was evil in the sight of the LORD and walked in the way of his father and in the way of his mother and in the way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who made Israel to sin.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('ESV', '1 Kings', 22, 53, 'He served Baal and worshiped him and provoked the LORD, the God of Israel, to anger in every way that his father had done.');
